  (530,170,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:330:\"<p>We are pleased to inform you that <strong> on 29 <sup>th</sup> and 30 <sup>th</sup> of April </strong> St. Petersburg will host another conference <strong>Application Developer Days</strong> in partnership with <strong>Qulix Systems</strong> . The conference is organized by SQALab Ltd. (Moscow) and BYTE-force (Yaroslavl).</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:2541:\"<h1>Application Developer Days 2011: programmers of all platforms, socialize!</h1>\r\n<p>We are pleased to inform you that <strong>on 29<sup>th</sup> and 30<sup>th</sup> of April</strong> St. Petersburg will host another conference <strong>Application Developer Days</strong> in partnership with <strong>Qulix Systems</strong>. The conference is organized by SQALab Ltd. (Moscow) and BYTE-force (Yaroslavl).</p>\r\n<div class=\"CenterImg\"><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" width=\"550px\" src=\"/uploaded/image/news/add2011-logo.png\" ilo-full-src=\"/uploaded/image/news/add2011-logo.png\" /></div>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://addconf.ru/\" target=\"_blank\">What is Application Developer Days?</a></strong> This is the only CIS IT-event that is not restricted to a specific technology or platform. The conference brings together reports on a variety of topics, which allows participants to have a look at different development tools, compare their advantages and disadvantages.</p>\r\n<p>The principal difference between Application Developer Days and other IT-conferences is the practical focus of the reports and interaction with the speakers.</p>\r\n<p>The conference will discuss the following key aspects:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Software architecture</li>\r\n<li>Coding techniques</li>\r\n<li>Development environments</li>\r\n<li>Programming technologies</li>\r\n<li>Trends</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>It is expected that the conference will be attended by experts from a number of prominent Russian and foreign companies such as Microsoft, IBM, Sun, Adobe, HP and some others, by IT-advisers and consulting agencies, and by representatives of field-specific university departments.</p>\r\n<h2>Application Developer Days has the following objectives:</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Dissemination of best practices and experience in the field of software engineering</li>\r\n<li>Initiation of long-term partnering contacts between participants</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Specialists who work with various software platforms and tools will have a chance to tell their colleagues about their projects, share experiences, learn about new approaches and possibilities. Each participant has an opportunity to make a report or presentation, to participate in roundtable discussions or seminars, to find new partners, and to get professional answers to topical questions.</p>\r\n<p>Hurry to register for the conference <a href=\"http://it-conf.ru/ru/confreg/index.htm\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> and look for your name in the list of accepted reports.</p>\r\n<p>See you in St. Petersburg!</p>\";}'),
  (531,170,111,'April 11, 2011'),
  (532,170,110,'Application Developer Days 2011: programmers of all platforms, socialize!'),
  (533,171,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:214:\"<p>For Qulix Systems the passed year of the Tiger was as stripy as tiger&rsquo;s skin. Successful projects had their ins and outs, difficulties eventually turned into new experience, a new phase of development.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:4599:\"<h1>2010 for Qulix Systems: What It Was Like</h1>\r\n<p>For Qulix Systems the passed year of the Tiger was as stripy as tiger&rsquo;s skin. Successful projects had their ins and outs, difficulties eventually turned into new experience, a new phase of development.</p>\r\n<p>One of the most remarkable achievements of the year 2010 is taking the interstate level. Qulix Systems won the open tender for the development of the CIS humane portal. Scope statement preparation is currently under way, while the project has already been announced to the heads of state.</p>\r\n<blockquote class=\"clearfix\"><img src=\"/uploaded/image/team/vti_small.jpg\" height=\"120\" width=\"86\" /> Further, we had an order for the creation of the Unified Legal Acts Register which is much in demand by all Commonwealth authorities. Thorough analysis and data structuring were completed within a short period of three-four months, which characterizes us as a well-organized team of professionals who can quickly tackle all the set tasks,&rsquo; says Valery Tikhonovich, Deputy General Manager.</blockquote>\r\n<h2>Pushing Back The Frontiers</h2>\r\n<p>Last year Java Department broadened the geography of workflow projects. In particular, this was reflected in increased usage of EMC Documentum and ECM Alfresco in both old and new domains. According to Project Manager Sergey Pupkevich, this will offer a possibility to provide more flexible and more optimal workflow automation solutions in the future.</p>\r\n<h2>QA Team: Looking Into The Future With Optimism</h2>\r\n<p>For the QA team this year, too, was a lucky one. There were a number of successfully-completed projects in independentsoftware testing for new big customers. The latter half of the year was marked by a dramatic upturn in demand from one of the Company&rsquo;s strategic partners.</p>\r\n<blockquote class=\"clearfix\"><img src=\"/uploaded/image/team/azh_small.jpg\" height=\"120px\" /> &lsquo;I am happy to say that there are new promising young specialists in the team and some of our long-time team members are back from maternity leave. Excellent professional training of the team and the growing demand for QA services make us feel positive about the future,&rsquo; notes Alexander Zhendinsky, Head of the Test Department, speaking about the year in view.</blockquote>\r\n<h2>They Fought For Qulix&hellip;</h2>\r\n<p>It was an uneasy but productive year in terms of mobile app development. New projects, new partners, new problems to face and new ways to sort them out.</p>\r\n<blockquote>&lsquo;They fought for Qulix'' is the most accurate description as regards the activity of the Mobile Solutions Department. But in the end all tasks, both technical and financial, were successfully finished, a big thank-you to everyone for that. We have finally built ourselves into a team capable of reaching any goal,&rsquo; states Dmitry Yankovich, Head of Mobile Solutions Department.</blockquote>\r\n<h2>Magis, melius, effectivius!</h2>\r\n<blockquote class=\"clearfix\"><img src=\"/uploaded/image/team/asl_small.jpg\" height=\"120px\" /> &lsquo;Cognition comes through comparison. And in the beginning of a new year you always wish to have a chance to proudly say &lsquo;magis, melius, effectivius &rsquo;at its end; moreover, you don&rsquo;t want just bare figures telling you about the growth, you want to feel it. And this year it turned out well! The Company was going up, so did the expertise, so did the number of particularly interesting projects and customers. So that we have only positive moments of the past year stuck in our memory. And the new year inspires the incredible feeling that the sky is the limit.&rsquo; We can hardly object to the words of Alexander Sliborsky, Head of Microsoft Technologies Department.</blockquote>\r\n<h2>Full Speed Ahead!</h2>\r\n<p>Year-end status proves that Qulix Systems has taken another step to achieve progress. The Company is expanding, offering new services, taking up fresh ideas, and broadening its geography.</p>\r\n<blockquote class=\"clearfix\"><img src=\"/uploaded/image/team/aar_small.jpg\" height=\"120px\" /> &lsquo;It&rsquo;s been another year remarkable for its victories and accomplishments. We don&rsquo;t stop at what&rsquo;s been done and keep movingforward, perfecting our work processes and ourselves to make the next year even more fruitful!&rsquo; said Alexander Arabey, Head of Business Development, summing up the results of 2010.</blockquote>\r\n<p>May the year 2011 bring Qulix Systems yet more profitable projects, interesting clients and climbing to new heights! With such potential this might feel like child&rsquo;s play.</p>\";}'),
  (534,171,111,'January 20, 2011'),
  (535,171,110,'2010 for Qulix Systems: What It Was Like'),
  (536,172,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:188:\"<p>Qulix Systems acted as an active participant and sponsor of the 8th International Conference Software Quality Assurance Days held on 19-20th November 2010 in St. Petersburg, Russia.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1880:\"<h2>QA Days 2010: afterword</h2>\r\n<p>Qulix Systems acted as an active participant and sponsor of the 8th International Conference Software <a href=\"http://it-conf.ru/ru/content/294.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Quality Assurance Days</a> held on 19-20th November 2010 in St. Petersburg, Russia.</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"Software Quality Assurance Days is an opportunity to make a name for yourself, to share experience, to learn about the latest trends and developments thus increasing your competitive advantage. The conference agenda was filled with the names of celebrity spokespersons and seemingly  little known but genuinely business-related areas of discussion. Should you ask me if the event is worth participating, my answer will be a definite \"Yes\" for both professionals and beginners in software testing\".</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Evelina Tananaeva, Senior QA Engineer</p>\r\n<p>During the two-day conference one could attend workshops run by such leading experts as Alexander Orlov, Stas Fomin and Vyacheslav Pankratov; hear about success stories from various areas of software development; examine and discuss research reports, participate in roundtable and panel discussions and even get involved in the presentation of a QA guru  Michael Bolton!</p>\r\n<p>We couldn&rsquo;t stay on the sidelines and miss the chance to present our state-of-the-art developments in this field. The secrets of mobile QA were revealed by Evelina Tananaeva. Olga Balashenko described to whom and under what circumstances it might be necessary to get testing engineers involved in tasks different from testing.</p>\r\n<p>The SQA Days Conference is held twice a year and bringing together more than 300 QA specialists from Russia, Ukraine, Belarus, Moldova and Kazakhstan. More useful contacts, more stare-of-the-art technologies, more benefits!</p>\r\n<p>See you next spring at the SQA Days!</p>\";}'),
  (537,172,111,'December 2, 2010'),
  (538,172,110,'QA Days 2010: afterword'),
  (539,173,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:213:\"<p>Qulix Systems is proud to announce that its new website built on top-notch technologies has been launched. The website offers a new eye-catching look and feel, as well as enhanced content and functionality.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1768:\"<h1>Qulix Systems Has Launched Its New Website</h1>\r\n<p>Qulix Systems is proud to announce that its new website built on top-notch technologies has been launched. The website offers a new eye-catching look and feel, as well as enhanced content and functionality.</p>\r\n<p>Within the framework of the project the development team, consisting of best Qulix specialists, worked out new modern and stylish design of the website as well as a new website concept, which fully corresponded to the business strategy of the company and answered its purposes.</p>\r\n<p>One of the powerful features of the website is its easy navigation. Our aim is to make it easy for visitors to feel comfortable while spending time on our website. That&rsquo;s why we have done our best to simplify the process of information search &ndash; you can quickly find necessary facts and details using the search form. The detailed description of services, provided by Qulix&rsquo; team, and software solutions, developed by the company, is available on the website along with project case studies and screenshots.</p>\r\n<p>Besides, you will always be able to fully enjoy the look and functions of the website despite the resolution of your monitor - the website automatically adjusts to different screens.</p>\r\n<p>We take care of our customers and have always been aiming at providing them with prompt feedback to their inquiries. Now you are able to get in touch with the company&rsquo;s representatives via Skype directly from the website pages as well as to reach them at their personal e-mail addresses.</p>\r\n<p>And many others&hellip;</p>\r\n<p>We hope that the visitors of new Qulix website will find it attractive and easy in browsing.</p>\r\n<p>We welcome you to enjoy our new online resource.</p>\";}'),
  (540,173,111,'November 20, 2009'),
  (541,173,110,'Qulix Systems Has Launched Its New Website'),
  (542,174,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:234:\"<p>Quality and performance of software development processes are directly dependent on complexity of projects and aggravation of competition on the IT-market. This issue becomes particularly vital amid the global financial crisis.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:7363:\"<h1>Qulix Systems Has Summarized its Work for the Year 2008</h1>\r\n<p>Quality and performance of software development processes are directly dependent on complexity of projects and aggravation of competition on the IT-market. This issue becomes particularly vital amid the global financial crisis.</p>\r\n<p>Current customers require services being provided by true professionals, who are able to demonstrate a deep knowledge of the IT-market and flexibility in responding to their queries.</p>\r\n<p>Software Quality Assurance has always been on the top for Qulix Systems since the Company''s foundation. For the years of its operating the Company has gained significant experience working with various customers, projects and communication models. In 2008 the Company put a priority on maintaining its customers and quality improvement of implemented projects.</p>\r\n<p>Qulix Systems keeps turning its business to \"smart\" services and the public sector demand for contemporary automation is the motive force of this turn.</p>\r\n<p>Maturity of Qulix Systems is proved by the fact that the Company was given the title of a High-Technology Park Resident and the status of an \"Inforpark\" Association member in 2008. The governmental support of the Company is an evidence of Qulix'' stability and prove of high quality of the services provided by the Company.</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"Getting of the High-Technology Park Resident status has become the admission of our merits. We have made the big time in IT-outsourcing of the republic. Moreover, we have been keeping this direction for a long time improving quality of the provided services and qualifications of our specialists, collaborating with Belarusian universities. As a High Technology Park resident we actively expand our activities, attract new customers and promote professional development of our specialists. Therefore, offer of miscellaneous IT-services is among main goals of the Company this year.\"</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Alexey Makarov, CEO</p>\r\n<p>Within the program of expanding regional presence Qulix Systems opened a new business-class office in the centre of Minsk and continued forming a team of highly qualified specialists. By the end of the year more than a third of Qulix software developers obtained Microsoft.NET and Sun Java Platform certificates. This made it possible to implement complex products using the newest technologies.</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"The Company endeavors to be in the van of the technology development. More than a half of the projects are implemented using the newest products and technologies. We monitor and analyze all the changes in the area of technologies that could influence development of the IT-market. Qulix Management adjust the development strategy of the Company on the basis of the obtained information in order to ensure a leader position of Qulix in the area of innovative IT-solutions. The main platforms the Company specializes in are Java and .NET. The Company gained a huge experience in working with them.\"</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Igor Sheverov, CTO</p>\r\n<p>In 2008 the Company fixed its stable business positions and successfully completed about 100 projects for more than 40 clients all over the world. It is remarkable that the third part of the customers is new to the Company. At the same time, regular clients, collaborating with Qulix for more than one year, remain one of the main Qulix values.</p>\r\n<p>According to the VP of Business Development Alexander Arabey, the number of Qulix customers grew due to Baltic and Scandinavian countries in 2008. The Company also expanded its presence on the UK IT-market. On the one hand, these regions offer a high level development of IT-services, on the other, they are uptight about outsourcing.</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"We faced many difficulties trying to enter these markets, but all of them have been mastered.\"</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Alexander Arabey, VP of Business Development</p>\r\n<p>The outlet for major public customers and the launch of new software development technologies are among the main trends for Qulix Systems this year. The Company has refocused its business from the corporate information systems development to the development of public sector systems, viz. social network, entertaining and information resources, based on delivering media content to mobile devices.</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"During the past year we actively developed GPS services. The range of the implemented products was diverse enough. In association with a well-known English company we developed the service that helped people to get emergency care in case of an accident pushing a single button on their cell phones. No one knows how many lives were saved thanks to this solution&hellip; As usual, we also cannot go without the programs that help business owners to control their employees, wives - their husbands, mothers - their children.\"</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Dmitry Yankovich, Director of Mobile Solutions Department</p>\r\n<p>These projects are not only an opportunity to gain invaluable experience for the Company, but at the same time a strong pride for the team members involved into the implementation.</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"I would like to mention some terms: a highly-distributed, loosely-coupled network, a common control centre, synchronization, guaranteed delivery. An integrator will understand that there''s a kind of extreme there. Thanks to the teamwork of the software architects, business analysts and developers we have fulfilled the customer''s ideas: designed an optimal architecture of the system and its components, unified the exchange protocols, provided a cross platform environment for the system operation, added an asynchronous connection with mobile devices. But our main achievement is putting the media network into test operation.\"</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Serge Zhirko, Senior Project Manager</p>\r\n<p>In 2008 Qulix Systems also managed to sum up its experience in the sphere of logistic system building, gained for the previous years. The Company has been developing such systems for more than 5 years. The ability to adapt the system quickly to new businesses has become the main aim of the optimisaion.</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"The project we are now implementing is a strategic investment of the Company to the area of delivery management systems for the years immediately ahead and now serves as the basis for the development of similar solutions. At the moment the system, built on the advanced technological platform, is in test operation. The solution has already received a number of positive responses from both technical specialists and ultimate users for its usability, high performance and scalability.\"</blockquote>\r\n<p>Alexander Sliborsky, Manager of MS Technologies Department</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"The year 2008 was successful for both the Company in general and its departments: we joined the High Technology Park and were given a title of its resident, won several tenders, opened a new office and implemented a number of projects. This year we hope that we will manage to make much of our success. Moreover, the Company has all necessary resources to reach this aim. In particular, we are planning to keep broadening our business geography and launch some new high quality business solutions.\"</blockquote>\";}'),
  (543,174,111,'January 21, 2009'),
  (544,174,110,'Qulix Systems Has Summarized its Work for the Year 2008'),
  (545,175,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:234:\"<p>Quality and performance of software development processes are directly dependent on complexity of projects and aggravation of competition on the IT-market. This issue becomes particularly vital amid the global financial crisis.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:3778:\"<h1>The 4th International Conference SQA Days-2008 Was Held in Minsk with Information Support of Qulix Systems</h1>\r\n<p>On the 17th of November the 4th International Conference of Software Quality Assurance Specialists SQA DAYS-2008 was held in the educational center IBB (Minsk, Belarus). More than 350 representatives of the leading IT-companies of Belarus and neighboring countries took part in the conference.</p>\r\n<p>Among the participants one could see QA Engineers, project managers as well as teachers and docents of the universities which prepare students of IT professions. They all got a nice possibility to communicate and exchange the experience with the best IT companies on the actual issues in quality assurance.</p>\r\n<p>The conference was organized by SQALab Company from Moscow in cooperation with the leading Belarusian IT companies and governmental organizations. Thanks to the fruitful cooperation of Belarusian, Russian and Ukrainian experts we managed to sum up the interesting reports of the speakers and stir up an active discussion. All participants expressed their gratitude to the organizers of the conference and the desire to participate in the following conferences.</p>\r\n<p>The chairman of SQA Days-2008 organization committee and CEO of SQALab, Vladislav Orlikov, Moscow, Russia, expressed his gratitude and hopes for the future cooperation:</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"The 4th international conference SQA Days-2008 succeeded in Minsk! It''s such a pleasure to realize that the conference got positive references and aroused a lively interest not only of the commercial organizations but of governmental ones as well. I''d like to thank all the participants and partners of the conference with the help of whom everything that had been planned fulfilled.  I''d like to express a special gratitude to Qulix Systems representatives who played an important role in organizing the conference and who conducted the main sections of it. Natalia Hustyr and Yulia Baranova could create comfortable and business like atmosphere for effective communication. I hope that there will be more projects of that kind in future which we''ll fulfill in close cooperation with Belarusian and Russian companies. I hope the conference was a valuable contribution to the development and prosperity of your business.\"</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Vladislav Orlikov, CEO of SQALab (Moscow, Russia)</p>\r\n<p>At SQA Days-2008 conference Qulix Systems was presented by two speakers Nataila Hustyr and Olga Balashenko. Their reports \"Bring Up Your QA Engineer\" and \"The Reasons For Troubles At The Projects\" presented in the form of flip-chart sessions provoked a lively discussion. The audience bombarded the speakers with questions trying to satisfy their curiosity.</p>\r\n<p>The member of the organization committee and the project manager of Qulix Systems, Natalia Hustyr expressed her point of view on the participation in the conference:</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"I''m glad that several months of active preparations were not spent in vain. Honestly, we felt a bit nervous about how Minsk audience would perceive the project of that kind. And we were extremely surprised when more than 350 people were overwhelmed by the presented reports. Flip-chart sessions during the brakes made a strong impression on the participants. We saw that this active way of communication appealed to people. There''s a strong need for face-to-face communication: round-table talks, workshops, flip-chart discussions. And we''ll take it into consideration while preparing next conferences. I''d like to thank all my colleagues from the other countries who managed to come and present their reports and to all the participants. We''ll put much effort to make the next conference even better.\"</blockquote>\";}'),
  (546,175,111,'November 20, 2008'),
  (547,175,110,'The 4th International Conference SQA Days-2008 Was Held in Minsk with Information Support of Qulix Systems'),
  (548,176,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:371:\"<p>The 4th International Conference of Software Quality Assurance Specialists will be held in Minsk on the 17th of November 2008 with the information support of Qulix Systems. That Conference will be of interest to QA engineers, software developers and analysts, technical writes, architects, project managers and top managers and all people interested in this field.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1323:\"<h1>Qulix Systems Will Provide the Information Support to IT-CONF SQA Days-2008</h1>\r\n<p>The 4th International Conference of Software Quality Assurance Specialists will be held in Minsk on the 17th of November 2008 with the information support of Qulix Systems. That Conference will be of interest to QA engineers, software developers and analysts, technical writes, architects, project managers and top managers and all people interested in this field.</p>\r\n<p>The Conference will be devoted to the issues related to testing and quality improvement of the software notably functional testing, processing power testing, test automation, configurational testing, usability and security testing, static quality improvement methods and other issues that will be of interest to IT-specialists.</p>\r\n<p>The aim of the Conference is to summarize the international know-how in the field of quality improvement and to create the basis for co-operation to actualize mutual projects in the field of testing that presupposes the possibility of information interchange and improvement of educational attainment for each specialist.</p>\r\n<p>That Conference will be of interest to QA engineers, software developers and analysts, technical writes, architects, project managers and top managers and all people interested in this field.</p>\";}'),
  (549,176,111,'September 05, 2008'),
  (550,176,110,'Qulix Systems Will Provide the Information Support to IT-CONF SQA Days-2008'),
  (551,177,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:342:\"<p>On June 21st 2008 at the Sports Club in Minsk countryside Qulix Systems team has celebrated its Birthday. There were over 120 people - employees of Minsk office, Moscow partners and guests- enjoying the show. The solar flying weather, informal dialogue and fine mood have created a special atmosphere and have made the rest remembered.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1782:\"<h1>Qulix Systems Has Ccelebrated its Birthday at the Sports Club</h1>\r\n<p>On June 21st 2008 at the Sports Club in Minsk countryside Qulix Systems team has celebrated its Birthday. There were over 120 people - employees of Minsk office, Moscow partners and guests- enjoying the show. The solar flying weather, informal dialogue and fine mood have created a special atmosphere and have made the rest remembered.</p>\r\n<p>For the last year Qulix Systems has considerably expanded their activity in the sphere of Belarus and foreign IT-services, has concluded new partner agreements and has won a number of tenders. Now the company is conducting active work above new challenging projects.</p>\r\n<p>Alexey Makarov, CEO of Qulix Systems, has started the official part:</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"I want to thank all employees for high-powered work and I wish everyone and the company as a whole successes, well-being, prosperity and movement only forward. Marking today a list of our achievements, it would be desirable to emphasize, that they were provided with the contribution of each of us. I am glad, that our team is the united mechanism, the united command possessing the united spirit of Qulix\".</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Alexey Makarov, CEO</p>\r\n<p>The all daylong celebration included many special activities. Among the favorites were volleyball, football and shooting. But the highlight of the program was paintball and all-terrain vehicle driving. During the competitions participants had to show force, fast reaction, harmonious coordination and also those qualities which help with daily work - to find an optimum, fast and true way to the purpose.</p>\r\n<p>Sports, drive, energy, fireworks and positive emotions - so there passed celebrating Qulix Systems Birthday.</p>\";}'),
  (552,177,111,'June 23, 2008'),
  (553,177,110,'Qulix Systems Has Ccelebrated its Birthday at the Sports Club'),
  (554,178,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:342:\"<p>On June 21st 2008 at the Sports Club in Minsk countryside Qulix Systems team has celebrated its Birthday. There were over 120 people - employees of Minsk office, Moscow partners and guests- enjoying the show. The solar flying weather, informal dialogue and fine mood have created a special atmosphere and have made the rest remembered.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:3320:\"<h1>Qulix Systems Becomes a Member of High-Technologies Park</h1>\r\n<p>In the end of April, 2008 Qulix Systems was granted a membership in High-Technologies Park (HTP) of the Republic of Belarus. The ground for the affirmative decision became the business project \"Services of offshore software development, meeting the requirements of consumers\", presented to the HTP administration.</p>\r\n<p>During the years of its existence Qulix Systems accumulated vast experience in creating high-tech solutions based on Sun, Microsoft and IBM platforms. For the time being the company provides a wide range of services in offshore custom software development, performs software systems or modules development based on customers requirements, and proactively designs and creates off-the-shelf software, using its expertise in subject and technology areas.</p>\r\n<p>Company development strategy is directed to ensuring high quality of provided services, continual personnel training, young specialists'' recruitment and active promotion of outsourcing services.</p>\r\n<p>Unique mix of corporate values, enthusiasm, qualified staff, individual approach to each project and client, ISO 9001 compliant processes and innovative technologies is the key factor of Qulix Systems success. In 2006 a consecutive audit in accordance with Capability Maturity Model Integration (CMMI) was performed. According to the results Qulix Systems is at the third level, which confirmed the maturity of its software development processes.</p>\r\n<p>The first half of 2008 became a turning point in company development. First Qulix Systems announced its expansion and new office opening in the center of Minsk. Next Qulix System became a member of Science and Technology Association \"Infopark\". And in the end of April, 2008 it was granted a membership in High-Technologies Park (HTP) of the Republic of Belarus. The ground for the affirmative decision became the business project \"Services of offshore software development, meeting the requirements of consumers\", presented to the HTP administration.</p>\r\n<p>Accession to HTP makes Qulix Systems even more competitive on the domestic and foreign markets of IT-services, bolsters company image and opens perspectives for further prosperous development due to state support, which increases company attractiveness not only for the clients, but for potential employees as well. Membership in professional associations and state support inspires confidence in Qulix Systems as future business partner.</p>\r\n<blockquote>Nowadays in Qulix we strive for intensive assurance of our services quality, continuous training and professional progress of our personnel, work with young specialists and cooperate with institution of higher education. As a member of High-Technologies Park we plan to expand our activity through active development of new business areas and projects. Also we are planning an increase in our personnel wages and creation of new working places. The latter is very important for us considering swift global development of IT-sphere and the need to provide our young talents with a possibility to fulfill themselves. We value every employee in our company. This very fact is an important incentive for our progress, and accession to HTP is a natural milestone in company development\"</blockquote>\";}'),
  (555,178,111,'May 13, 2008'),
  (556,178,110,'Qulix Systems Becomes a Member of High-Technologies Park'),
  (557,179,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:404:\"<p>To comply with strict selection requirements Qulix System management decided to concentrate its efforts on attaining formal maturity criteria, one of which is personnel certification. It will provide competitive advantage on local and international markets, help securing leadership in innovative IT-solutions, increase technology expertise, and demonstrate adequate procedures of quality control.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1873:\"<h1>Qulix Systems Enhances its IT-services Quality</h1>\r\n<p>To comply with strict selection requirements Qulix System management decided to concentrate its efforts on attaining formal maturity criteria, one of which is personnel certification. It will provide competitive advantage on local and international markets, help securing leadership in innovative IT-solutions, increase technology expertise, and demonstrate adequate procedures of quality control.</p>\r\n<p>Modern business becomes inseparable with information technologies. Companies seek for a long-term reliable partnership with IT-vendors that are able to provide top-notch services, and one of the formal criteria of selecting a partner is highly skilled specialists.</p>\r\n<p>For the time being more than a quarter of Qulix Systems developers obtained Microsoft certificates in.NET (.NET Framework 2.0 Web Applications и .NET Framework 2.0 Windows) and Sun certificates in Java (Sun Certified Programmer for the Java 2 Platform, Standard Edition 5.0). Also active training is performed for the following certifications: .NET Framework 2.0 Distributed Applications, Web Developer, Windows Developer, Enterprise Applications Developer, Sun Certified Developer for Java 2 Platform, Standard Edition.</p>\r\n<p>Company intentions are not confined by the stated above long-term goal. Qulix Systems aligns its activities in accordance with the latest tendencies of the world IT-market. Having domestic certified experts with deep knowledge and profound expertise in Microsoft .NET and Sun Java Platform allows creating complex, feature-rich products, based on the most up-to-date technologies.</p>\r\n<p>Our experience confirms that certification not only favors employee motivation and the possibility of advancement and growth, but improves the quality of work performed, which further affirms Qulix competencies.</p>\";}'),
  (558,179,111,'May 03, 2008'),
  (559,179,110,'Qulix Systems Enhances its IT-services Quality'),
  (560,180,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:374:\"<p>Qulix System became the member of Science and Technology Association \"Infopark\" as was enacted by the decision of the Association Council on February 28, 2008. \"Infopark\" is a voluntary community of leading IT development companies in the Republic of Belarus and was created to stimulate the progress of its members by creating favorable environment in the IT sphere.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1104:\"<h1>Qulix Systems Acceded to \"Infopark\" Association</h1>\r\n<p>Qulix System became the member of Science and Technology Association \"Infopark\" as was enacted by the decision of the Association Council on February 28, 2008. \"Infopark\" is a voluntary community of leading IT development companies in the Republic of Belarus and was created to stimulate the progress of its members by creating favorable environment in the IT sphere.</p>\r\n<p>All members of the Association shall meet high requirements in software development and testing domains, quality of service and personnel. Today \"Infopark\" unites 62 Belarusian and joint software development companies and enterprises and more than 9 000 SE professionals (70 % of all national IT specialists).</p>\r\n<p>Becoming the member of \"Infopark\" affirms that Qulix Systems meets the high requirements demanded from the members of Association. It will allow the company to strengthen its position and competitiveness in the software development market. Official membership certificate was presented to Alexey Makarov, CEO of Qulix Systems, on March 20, 2008.</p>\";}'),
  (561,180,111,'March 20, 2008'),
  (562,180,110,'Qulix Systems Acceded to \"Infopark\" Association'),
  (563,181,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:416:\"<p>The fast-growing demand for outsourcing services, vast experience of Qulix Systems in software development and QA along with persistent on-going efforts for quality improvement resulted in significant increase of customers and projects in the last year. A new modern office opening in the business center of Minsk and staff increase will be the next step in the company&rsquo;s advance/progress in the market.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1083:\"<h1>Qulix Systems Announces Company Expansion Plans</h1>\r\n<p>The fast-growing demand for outsourcing services, vast experience of Qulix Systems in software development and QA along with persistent on-going efforts for quality improvement resulted in significant increase of customers and projects in the last year. A new modern office opening in the business center of Minsk and staff increase will be the next step in the company&rsquo;s advance/progress in the market.</p>\r\n<p>Qulix Systems has announced two expansions during last years due to active penetration of high technologies in everyday life and booming growth of company&rsquo;s activities. The success of Qulix Systems is based on its commitment to quality products and personalized service.</p>\r\n<p>Due to staff increase Qulix Systems invites skilled project managers, software developers, and QA engineers, who are capable to meet the challenges and do teamwork effectively. In its turn the company will provide the maximum opportunities, resources, and support for you along with a comprehensive set of benefits.</p>\";}'),
  (564,181,111,'March 12, 2008'),
  (565,181,110,'Qulix Systems Announces Company Expansion Plans'),
  (566,182,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:224:\"<p>Programmer and QA Specialist Days were celebrated in Qulix Systems with sports and entertainment outdoor event in amusement park \"Dreamland\". It was attended by Qulix employees along with their children and relatives.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1854:\"<h1>Programmer Day + QA Specialist Day = Qulix Systems</h1>\r\n<p>Programmer and QA Specialist Days were celebrated in Qulix Systems with sports and entertainment outdoor event in amusement park \"Dreamland\". It was attended by Qulix employees along with their children and relatives.</p>\r\n<p>Working for an IT-company implies not just having definite skills and knowledge about your specialty. And not just the ability to do your work in time and efficiently. It implies also a team spirit which supports and gives confidence that each difficult situation can be settled with the assistance of colleagues. It''s a common knowledge that one of the professionalism components is the art to work for success of the whole team. This art is essential not only for managers who direct the work of the team but for common developers as well.</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"Each professional creates himself. In our company we do it together, valuing team and friendship. Events aimed at strengthening team spirit and which main idea is unity and cooperation are always actual. It is important for us to be aware of each person involvement into one company, stable and dynamic. We need to work out single goals, remove stress and strengthen the confidence between employees. That is why we organized Programmer''s Day outside of office and everyday routine\"</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Alexey Makarov, CEO</p>\r\n<p>The event activities featured active sport and game competitions in which everybody could take part. Volunteers could decorate themselves with body-art or get a caricature portrait from a professional painter. Many other activities were held including Anti-virus, Bug Tracking, tug-of-war, and knight contests with target and log throwing. Emulative spirit, adrenalin, and good moods accompanied every Qulix Systems member this bright September day.</p>\";}'),
  (567,182,111,'September 25, 2007'),
  (568,182,110,'Programmer Day + QA Specialist Day = Qulix Systems'),
  (569,183,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:214:\"<p>August 17, 2007 - Qulix Systems will be taking part in Business Internet conference (Delovoy Internet), scheduled for October 4-5, 2007, Minsk (Belarus) together with SEADMEX (dp Consulting) company, Russia.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1762:\"<h1>Qulix Will Participate in \"Business Internet\" Conference</h1>\r\n<p>August 17, 2007 - Qulix Systems will be taking part in Business Internet conference (Delovoy Internet), scheduled for October 4-5, 2007, Minsk (Belarus) together with SEADMEX (dp Consulting) company, Russia.</p>\r\n<p>Top-management of Qulix Systems has always been interested in obtaining and sharing software development expertise and such conferences were always a valuable means for that. Denis Petelin, the leading coach of SEADMEX (dp Consulting) was specially invited by Qulix Systems to present an expert analysis on software projects'' economics and significance of motivation on projects and business in general.</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"Business Internet conference is one of the biggest IT events in Belarus. The event will offer presentations from prominent industry analysts and thought leaders, breakout sessions, and real-world case studies. Such events have been a real help during the last 7 years on the way of acquiring necessary and valuable expertise in IT domain. SEADMEX (dp Consulting) has provided the best IT consultant in software domain, Denis Petelin. We have made the right choice initiating our cooperation\".</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Alexey Makarov, CEO</p>\r\n<p>Among the questions that will be lightened by Denis Petelin are the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>What is software project economics and what exactly money should be paid for?</li>\r\n<li>Why to talk about motivation (Resource Utilization and Billable Hrs, Hour Rate, EBIT, Fixed Price project, Time and Material project)?</li>\r\n<li>What is Customer Satisfaction. Customer Satisfaction = Delivery?</li>\r\n<li>Total sum assessment and some other cases when money are not a motive any more.</li>\r\n</ul>\";}'),
  (570,183,111,'September 19, 2007'),
  (571,183,110,'Qulix Will Participate in \"Business Internet\" Conference'),
  (572,184,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:587:\"<p>Belarus, Minsk, September 9, 2007 - This day was destined to be a QA specialist''s Day worldwide. That was a day when a \"computer bug\" is first identified and named by LT Grace Murray Hopper, Director of Programming Languages for the Office of the Chief of Naval Operations, while she was on Navy active duty in 1945. It was found in the Mark II Aiken Relay Calculator at Harvard University. The operators affixed the moth to the computer log, where it still resides, with the entry: \"First actual case of bug being found.\" They \"debugged\" the computer, first introducing the term.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:3059:\"<h1>Quality Assurance on the Edge - QA Specialist Day Celebration in Belarus</h1>\r\n<p>Belarus, Minsk, September 9, 2007 - This day was destined to be a QA specialist''s Day worldwide. That was a day when a \"computer bug\" is first identified and named by LT Grace Murray Hopper, Director of Programming Languages for the Office of the Chief of Naval Operations, while she was on Navy active duty in 1945. It was found in the Mark II Aiken Relay Calculator at Harvard University. The operators affixed the moth to the computer log, where it still resides, with the entry: \"First actual case of bug being found.\" They \"debugged\" the computer, first introducing the term.</p>\r\n<p>One may think that a Tester is an accidental helper on a software project and plays a minor role. But there is nothing not worthy paying attention to in that profession. Every detail and bug has to be found and taken into account in QA of a system''s run. This is what determines a qualified tester. The core thing here is not to worry much about ''friendly'' attacks of developers reckoning that a tester is a project enemy who delays projects termination.</p>\r\n<p>A good thing here is that such developers are few today though everybody knows about counteraction phenomenon which means that developers work for creation, QA testers - for breaking and finding bugs in their work. That is understandable but that statement doesn''t work for a good team. A software product quality can be provided only by a smoothly running work of every team member where QA specialists are a necessary part of it.</p>\r\n<p>There are lots of stories and myths in every occupation. QA is not an exception. QA Myths is one of the topics that are a part of QA introduction course which is regularly read by our company experts in Moscow companies and Minsk universities.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>First myth: QA equals Software Development Product Testing;</li>\r\n<p>This is not exactly the same thing. Testing process is a part of Quality Assurance. The lion''s share of QA goals is projects'' quality procurement. The project can be considered successfully performed when all of its components are carefully compiled and gathered as parts of Swiss watch. That means that every project participator is perfectly aware of his responsibilities, goals and targets.</p>\r\n<li>Second myth: A Tester job is much easier than a Developer''s occupation.</li>\r\n<p>Not true. I can site lots of examples as a back-balance to that statement. In that case I can say that people are getting mixed up with definition of a proficient TESTER and a PERSON who just clicks all the time. An expert in QA both is a programmer, analyst and manager at once. A whole baggage of knowledge needs to be under the belt in order to be a real pro in testing. Moreover, such a person is always a creative man who is able to lay out complicated tasks in a plain manner skillfully, thinks logically and sequentially, Alexander Zhendinsky, Qulix Systems Test Team Manager, narrated on Quality Assurance specialists'' Day Celebration in the company.</p>\r\n</ul>\";}'),
  (573,184,111,'September 10, 2007'),
  (574,184,110,'Quality Assurance on the Edge - QA Specialist Day Celebration in Belarus'),
  (575,185,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:587:\"<p>Belarus, Minsk, September 9, 2007 - This day was destined to be a QA specialist''s Day worldwide. That was a day when a \"computer bug\" is first identified and named by LT Grace Murray Hopper, Director of Programming Languages for the Office of the Chief of Naval Operations, while she was on Navy active duty in 1945. It was found in the Mark II Aiken Relay Calculator at Harvard University. The operators affixed the moth to the computer log, where it still resides, with the entry: \"First actual case of bug being found.\" They \"debugged\" the computer, first introducing the term.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:4438:\"<h1>Business Development Leader Strategies</h1>\r\n<p>That is a common fact that a leader''s value is based on their individual productivity, the productivity of their direct reports, and their ability to retain those direct reports. Great leaders demonstrate their value by incurring fewer costs while simultaneously increasing profit. Business Development is one of the most important issues in any company. In Qulix Systems Alexander Arabey executes Director of Business Development role.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Bold\">VLE:</span> What''s the value of leadership in your understanding?<br /> <span class=\"Bold\">AAR:</span> A leader is someone who brings out the best in us, who inspires us to do our best, who causes to think about the longer term, the bigger picture. A leader is someone who causes us to focus not on the obstacles but on how to get things done especially in business domain. This is someone who has sheer force in his deeds so strategic planning helps to go with the times. A leadership is a visionary who has the ability to articulate goals, business objectives, and aspirations. A leader must also have an appreciation of the differences in people - not only in gender or race, but in views or philosophy. This is especially important in IT nowadays as we know that IT domain is rapidly growing.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Bold\">VLE:</span> And who is a successful leader?<br /> <span class=\"Bold\">AAR:</span> A successful leader must have a sense of who the people in his company are and where they come from. This is not only awareness about their knowledge base and set of skills but their personal characteristics as well.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Bold\">VLE:</span> Conventional corporate structure is challenged to keep up with the rate of change in the marketplace. Creating a vision and a direction is more important than ever. What are the most important aspects in Business development?<br /> <span class=\"Bold\">AAR:</span> Well, first of all this is Business Plan Design and Development. A current and well-designed formal business plan is the foundation of any successful business. Sometime sit is not easy to convey excellent ideas into a fully developed business plan. It then becomes a living document that requires constant monitoring and customization to meet existing and emerging business opportunities. Then Strategic and Financial goal alignment follows. It is important to identify important ''Strategic Driver'' and critical success factors. Then Initiation and Formulation of Strategic Business partnerships go. These are relationships that leverage your visibility, capability, your market presence. It grows your business at a much faster pace.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Bold\">VLE:</span> Are there any specific approaches in Qulix Systems to running a business?<br /> <span class=\"Bold\">AAR:</span> The aim of Business development department of Qulix Systems is to make profitable and well-informed decisions about the IT market and launching of our new projects. We individually design each assignment to meet all requirements of our clients'' cost effectively. We explore all practical opportunities before finalizing the work and always endeavor to meet the spirit of a contract as well as meeting the agreed terms.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Bold\">VLE:</span> How to achieve extraordinary results with ordinary people and who are the ''Right People'' for the organization?<br /> <span class=\"Bold\">AAR:</span> Attracting and retaining people in today''s marketplace is a war for talents and the most important factor for success in today''s knowledge-based economy. Top-management of Qulix Systems and I personally maintain that superior talent potential is a prime source of competitive advantage. In the new economy competition is global, capital is abundant, ideas are developed quickly and people are willing to change jobs often. In that kind of environment all that matters is talent. Talent always wins. We consider every single employee as an extraordinary talented person. This factor is one of those that is determining our profitable work and successful collaboration with partners and clients worldwide.</p>\r\n<p>Alexander Arabey (AAR) is Director of Business Development at Qulix Systems and one of its founders. Alexander holds a master''s degree in business administration and a bachelor''s degree in computer sciences.</p>\r\n<p>Vera Leonik (VLE) is eMarketing Specialist at Qulix Systems.</p>\";}'),
  (576,185,111,'September 01, 2007'),
  (577,185,110,'Business Development Leader Strategies'),
  (578,186,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:236:\"<p>There are lots of custom software development companies with a special QA department of testers there. Qulix Systems is not an exception. Here is what one of the leading Test managers of Qulix Systems, Alexander Zhendinsky, says.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:11228:\"<h1>Quality Assurance on the Edge</h1>\r\n<p>There are lots of custom software development companies with a special QA department of testers there. Qulix Systems is not an exception. Here is what one of the leading Test managers of Qulix Systems, Alexander Zhendinsky, says.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Bold\">VLE:</span> What is your work experience as a developer and QA tester?<br /> <span class=\"Bold\">AZH:</span> To start I may say that I am a regular of State Belarusian University of Informatics and Radioelectronics (SBUIR), Minsk, Belarus, graduate where providing of lots of different information which is hard to cope with is a common thing. But the reverse of the medal is the following- knowledge gained there gives a real base which helps a young specialist to find himself in lots of areas which are not related to radioelectronics. In IT domain I came in after some time of working at Nokia service center and some trading companies - which is even more distant from QA then you can imagine. It was 5 years ago. There was no profound knowledge and practice of computer work in me at those days so lots of my time was spent on getting to know computer administration peculiarities except managing the main task of gaining QA tester proficiency. The start of my QA tester position was really quick. First I had a training practice during one day on Saturday after which I was provided with heaps of documentation and manuals to consult with. Second, on Monday I was already testing a system for one of our Belarusian clients. It was really exciting and challenging. QA profession is really exciting and you should not trust those who claim the opposite. My second project in IT domain was a real university of life. It was a project with foreign customers which was conducted strictly on RUP (Rational Unified Process) by an excellent management staff. Benefits of my participation in that project were obvious. It gave me experience of handling management pitfalls of working in teams, resource and process planning, that knowledge served as a foundation for my present-day work in a QA department of Qulix Systems.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Bold\">VLE:</span> What can you determine as the most difficult in QA?<br /> <span>AZH:</span> As for me, the most sore spot in QA is careless attitude of some project managers to necessity of testing in general. Some reckon that QA is almost a useless thing which is not worth paying attention to. They do not understand aims and priorities of testing. Think that proper QA performance is just a waist of time. But if to have a look at any worth-while project-management manual we will see 60-70% data of expense usually goes on QA from the whole cost of IT project development.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Bold\">VLE:</span> We know that there are lots of myths and stories in every occupation. What can you say about that?<br /> <span class=\"Bold\">AZH:</span> QA Myths - one of the topics that are a part of QA introduction course which is regularly read by our company experts in Moscow companies and Minsk universities.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>First myth: QA equals Software Development Product Testing.</li>\r\n<p>This is not exactly the same thing. Testing process is a part of Quality Assurance. The lion''s share of QA goals is projects'' quality procurement. The project can be considered successfully performed when all of its components are carefully compiled and gathered as parts of Swiss watch. That means that every project participator is perfectly aware of his responsibilities, goals and targets.</p>\r\n<li>Second myth: A Tester job is much easier than a Developer''s occupation.</li>\r\n<p>Not true. I can site lots of examples as a back-balance to that statement. In that case I can say that people are getting mixed up with definition of a proficient TESTER and a PERSON who just clicks all the time. An expert in QA both is a programmer, analyst and manager at once. A whole baggage of knowledge needs to be under the belt in order to be a real pro in testing. Moreover, such a person is always a creative man who is able to lay out complicated tasks in a plain manner skillfully, thinks logically and sequentially.</p>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span class=\"Bold\">VLE:</span> Is there is something not worthy paying attention in QA?<br /> <span class=\"Bold\">AZH:</span> Every detail has to be taken into account in QA of a system''s run. This is what determines a qualified tester. The core thing here is not to worry much about ''friendly'' attacks of your developers reckoning that a tester is a project enemy who delays projects termination. A good thing here is that such developers are few today though everybody knows counteraction phenomenon. Developers work for creation, QA testers - for breaking and finding bugs in their work. That is understandable but we are a good team though.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Bold\">VLE:</span> How did you personally stick to Quality Assurance?<br /> <span class=\"Bold\">AZH:</span> I was lucky to get to Qulix Systems when formalization of processes and the whole work in the company was at its beginning. The world of QA was also changing constantly, new methodologies were appearing and I was up to that with a real will. The work was complex and challenging. But when your brand-new ideas find positive feedback of colleagues and customers you are proud of yourself and feel really influential.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Bold\">VLE:</span> Does every software project need testers?<br /> <span class=\"Bold\">AZH:</span> If customers are interested in a successful realization of a project than I would strongly recommend presence of good testers. Bugs are a common place in a development process no matter what professional level programmers possess. The point here is only in quantity of bugs. Talking about statistics I may say that 90 % of all bugs are usually fixed by developers while code compiling process and launching a product. 10 % of them just can''t be found because of substandard situations in program'' run which can not be taken into account by developers. In some cases developers do not lift a hand in launching a written code to make sure that everything is ok. So testers are exactly what any development process always needs to secure the process and a company'' s name.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Bold\">VLE:</span> What kinds of testing should be considered on a project?<br /> <span class=\"Bold\">AZH:</span> There is no a well-defined answer here. The number of tests needed is a unique thing to define and primarily depends on a project itself, its requirements, terms and conditions of programming, the way future system will be running. But there are some common recommendations here. Testing process has to be started at the period of a project'' initiation. Technical and functional specifications should be checked. The beginning of a project is an important period that must not be omitted. All mistakes at that period can smoothly ruin further successful project development and system''s performance. Usually it saves time and money. Such efforts at the beginning reduce project''s costs.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Bold\">VLE:</span> What are common problems in the software development process?<br /> <span class=\"Bold\">AZH:</span> Well, it''s not easy to determine at once the most common ones. There are lots of them but a competent manager saves situation. Here are some pitfalls that usually occur: Ignorant project manager - the most crucial thing on a project. Problems with working hours and efforts assessment, goals allocation and performance audit, processes design easily supplement. Badly formulated system''s requirements, their incomprehensibility, incompleteness, ambiguity. Incorrectly chosen technologies for project development. Global changes in a project in the middle of the development process - system''s architecture and database structure alteration which drags out project terms and increases expenses.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Bold\">VLE:</span> What is software ''quality''?<br /> <span class=\"Bold\">AZH:</span> As for me this is a hookup of functional and technical system''s requirements fitness with final realization. Moreover a qualitative project is the one with great functional procurement and neither testers nor final users were able to find bugs and defaults.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Bold\">VLE:</span> How can it be known when to stop testing?<br /> <span class=\"Bold\">AZH:</span> Many modern software applications are so complex, and run in such an interdependent environment, that complete testing can never be done. Common factors in deciding when to stop are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Deadlines of a project;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases completed with certain percentage passed;</li>\r\n<li>Coverage of code/functionality/requirements reaches a specified point;</li>\r\n<li>Bug rate falls below a certain level;</li>\r\n<li>Beta or alpha testing period ends;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span class=\"Bold\">VLE:</span> Who is a good QA tester?<br /> <span class=\"Bold\">AZH:</span> This is not only a person with proper education (mathematics, informatics) with logical thinking and attention to details, but also a person who leaves and breathes for QA. In that case that job can be a dream career.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Bold\">VLE:</span> What Qulix Systems does to provide qualified and efficient QA performance?<br /> <span class=\"Bold\">AZH:</span> Qulix Systems always thinks about our testers'' professional level fitness on a global IT market. We cherish every newcomer and help in software development proficiency reach. First of all I may say that we are very thorough in our employees'' recruitment. This is a primary stage when those with not a high proficiency level are sifting out. Also we educate them. Seminars and trainings are conducted. Then we make a newbie a stand-by tester or developer with his own concrete tasks. That gives an opportunity to dive into the process at once. Results of his work can be easily seen and necessary hints and recommendations can be provided which reduces time spent and increases speed of their learning. We use the practices of special educational materials preparation by qualified testers. All of these we discuss during our seminars where the best new working practices are deciding to be used. One of the most determining facts which help our testers to gain experience is a challenging work with diverse project tasks. We try to make sure that every single tester knows how to be a functional tester, test-designer, automation tests developer, analyst and technical writer. One - year project of individual development and growth preparation is another useful thing we practice in Qulix Systems. When all of that is discussed a manager helps to intensify and streamline a newcomer''s professional growth.</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Bold\">VLE:</span> Thank you!</p>\r\n<p>AZH - Alexander Zhendinsky is Qulix Systems Test Team Manager, has 5 years experience in QA field, wide experience in development of test documentation - test plans, test suites, test cases, test surveys, test scenarios, etc; excellent knowledge of test methodologies, test and development processes, interaction and communication processes building between customers and test team.</p>\r\n<p>VLE - Vera Leonik, Qulix Systems eMarketing Specialist</p>\";}'),
  (579,186,111,'August 21, 2007'),
  (580,186,110,'Quality Assurance on the Edge'),
  (581,187,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:207:\"<p>A new status was given to our company - closed joint stock company Qulix Systems. Registration certificate was signed by Minsk State Executive Committee on June 21, 2007 - the birthday of the company.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:2082:\"<h1>Qulix Systems Gains a New Status on Belarusian IT Market</h1>\r\n<p>A new status was given to our company - closed joint stock company Qulix Systems. Registration certificate was signed by Minsk State Executive Committee on June 21, 2007 - the birthday of the company.</p>\r\n<p>Belarus, Minsk, August 8, 2007 - A new status was given to our company - closed joint stock company Qulix Systems. Registration certificate was signed by Minsk State Executive Committee on June 21, 2007 - the birthday of the company.</p>\r\n<p>Qulix Systems was operated as BelHard Group Corp. subdivision from June 21, 2000. From the very beginning Qulix Systems was launched as a company that provided QA domain services with QA automation solutions, software performance testing, functional testing and design, code and system''s processes audit. It was the first commercial area that served as a solid base for further development of Qulix Systems in the direction of software development and IT consulting. The company has gradually become an independent unit managing separate IT projects.</p>\r\n<p>Nowadays Qulix Systems is a Belarusian IT company, outsourcing custom software development, QA, and IT consulting provider. The company''s work is oriented both to Belarusian internal market, as well as Russian, European and USA marketplace. The main technological tendencies of Qulix Systems operation are complex systems'' development on J2EE and MS.NET platforms. Starting from 2005 a lot of efforts was also dedicated to mobile technologies development.</p>\r\n<p>During the 7 year period we have been growing as a team of like-minded people. A juridical status acquisition will confirm our unity and will become a new landmark for Qulix Systems'' further development. We appreciate BelHard''s providing a starting platform for us and our conjoint work during those years. Now we will be framing Belarusian IT market together. The fact that the registration document was signed on June 21, our company''s birthday, serves as our plans and goals confirmation, ''Alexey Makarov, CEO, Qulix Systems, said.</p>\";}'),
  (582,187,111,'August 08, 2007'),
  (583,187,110,'Qulix Systems Gains a New Status on Belarusian IT Market'),
  (584,188,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:416:\"<p>How important is knowledge over the course of your work life? Can you afford not to know? Qulix Systems'' staff has found that out.    Dennis Syropushchinsky, Business Analyst, has conducted a seminar on business analytics peculiar points for senior and junior staff of Qulix Systems, giving tips to help in building and sustaining knowledge base to achieve career success as a business analyst in the company.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:2193:\"<h1>Business Analytics Seminars in Qulix Systems</h1>\r\n<p>How important is knowledge over the course of your work life? Can you afford not to know? Qulix Systems'' staff has found that out.</p>\r\n<p>Dennis Syropushchinsky, Business Analyst, has conducted a seminar on business analytics peculiar points for senior and junior staff of Qulix Systems, giving tips to help in building and sustaining knowledge base to achieve career success as a business analyst in the company.</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"Giving our employees the essential knowledge is of primary importance for our company. Such seminars are a commonplace for Qulix Systems. We try to make them standing out from the crowd of the same ones provided by other educational business centers making them comprehensible and in down-to-earth communication manner. It helps to provide better presentation, higher quality, and better value. These points are stressing benefits for our staff dealing with business analytics primarily. Benefits count, not features. Benefits of such events are obvious for everyone, our guys and their managers. Qulix Systems focuses 100% on providing essential knowledge base for every talented employee\"</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Dennis Syropushchinsky, Business Analyst</p>\r\n<p>The topics covered at the seminar are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Business analytics is a long-term career strategy - what business analyses will do for you and for a company;</li>\r\n<li>How to stay in touch with strong business essence while balancing methods of dealing with demanding customers requirements;</li>\r\n<li>Methods of clarification and matching client''s demands;</li>\r\n<li>What is a core essence in the work of business analytics;</li>\r\n<li>Applied software necessary for business analyses;</li>\r\n<li>Main stages and steps in analytics of software development projects;</li>\r\n<li>Main instruments in managing confusing and unclear moments in projects;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\"Clearly, when business analytics instruments used correctly by an experienced and well - prepared company member, it can be a path to new business opportunities for a whole company and its industry domain notably\", participants of seminars claimed.</p>\";}'),
  (585,188,111,'July 12, 2007'),
  (586,188,110,'Business Analytics Seminars in Qulix Systems'),
  (587,189,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:434:\"<p>Qulix Systems will be taking part in an international \"Modern Java Technology Tendencies\" conference, scheduled for July 12, 2007, Minsk launched by High Technology Park (Belarus) and Exadel company. More that 300 belarusian and foreign IT professionals will be taking part in it. The main figures are- Gavin King (Australia), founder of a popular open-source Hibernate ORM and Max Anderson (Denmark), JBoss leading programmer.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1759:\"<h1>\"Modern Java Technology Tendencies\" Conference</h1>\r\n<p>Qulix Systems will be taking part in an international \"Modern Java Technology Tendencies\" conference, scheduled for July 12, 2007, Minsk launched by High Technology Park (Belarus) and Exadel company. More that 300 belarusian and foreign IT professionals will be taking part in it. The main figures are- Gavin King (Australia), founder of a popular open-source Hibernate ORM and Max Anderson (Denmark), JBoss leading programmer.</p>\r\n<p>The conference program was designed with the intention to discuss newly emerged opportunities of Java technology usage where Hibernate, JSF and Seam are the newcomers.</p>\r\n<p>The main points of the conference are new opportunities of Java, new tendencies of its development and usage. Discussions and conversations with top IT professionals from \"Hibernate\", \"JSF\", \"Seam\", \"RichFaces\", \"Ajax4JSF\", \"Red Hat Developer Studio\" and Q &amp; A on this topic are going to be the hottest moments of the conference.</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"There were lots of discussions about the necessity of new frameworks and the presence of JSP, Struts, Tapestry and others. There is a simple answer here - such applications demand monotonous and boring work of program developers which has nothing to in common with writing a code for business solution. Besides there are no IDE for the overwhelming majority of frameworks which are usually make the coding easier. That is why Hibernate, JSF, Seam are making lives of our developers easier and their work more productive. New source of information in this field is another fresh breath in Java and in our company developers'' success and knowledge database\"</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Alexey Makarov, CEO (Qulix Systems)</p>\";}'),
  (588,189,111,'July 10, 2007'),
  (589,189,110,'\"Modern Java Technology Tendencies\" Conference'),
  (590,190,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:371:\"<p>For 7 years of its existence Qulix Systems has grown up from a newbie to one of the leading software development companies in Belarus. One of the determinative driving factors for its growth was an active position in quality assurance of software products and innovations that were regularly introduced into marketing politics and client services of Qulix Systems.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:2217:\"<h1>Qulix Systems: 7 Years of Quality</h1>\r\n<p>For 7 years of its existence Qulix Systems has grown up from a newbie to one of the leading software development companies in Belarus. One of the determinative driving factors for its growth was an active position in quality assurance of software products and innovations that were regularly introduced into marketing politics and client services of Qulix Systems.</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"We have been working for seven years with the intention of making software and mobile solutions available for a greater number of interested customers. We constantly used new types of services, introduced innovative approaches to software solutions development, explored and implemented new technological platforms and top-notch solutions for quality support. A new stage in the company''s development allows us to gain a new vision of mission of Qulix Systems - always provide excellent quality of our software solutions and competitive advantage to our customers on a world market. The direction for providing quality and front line approaches in all areas of the company''s activities was determined as a way-to-go for the future company''s strategic development\".</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Alexey Makarov, CEO (Qulix Systems)</p>\r\n<p>Pricing policy of Qulix Systems together with high quality of services provided provides additional competitive advantages to our clients. The company is actively expanding the scope of its activities and entering new markets. Last year a new representative office in the United Kingdom was opened.</p>\r\n<p>Quality procurement is one of the important competitive advantages of Qulix Systems that has always been of paramount importance. The company releases new software solutions, expands new and advanced technological opportunities for its clients and is an active participant of all processes aimed to provide understanding and knowledge of high-tech necessity for a prosperous business development in Belarus today.</p>\r\n<p>Prosperous results of the company''s growth are acknowledged in its increasing income. Qulix Systems today is an independent business unit which successfully represents IT brand in CIS countries and Europe.</p>\";}'),
  (591,190,111,'June 28, 2007'),
  (592,190,110,'Qulix Systems: 7 Years of Quality'),
  (593,191,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:194:\"<p>Qulix Systems has spent at one of the picturesque places near Minsk. Informal, amicable atmosphere, thematic evening party, beautiful weather, sunshine, fellowship and fireworks at night.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1801:\"<h1>Qulix Systems Has Celebrated its 7th Birthday</h1>\r\n<p>Qulix Systems has spent at one of the picturesque places near Minsk. Informal, amicable atmosphere, thematic evening party, beautiful weather, sunshine, fellowship and fireworks at night.</p>\r\n<p>During 7 years of its existence Qulix Systems has grown up from a newbie to one of the leading software development companies in Belarus. There has been a lot of professional work and even more of substandard and innovative approaches to business. But what is the most important - there has always been and will be a friendly and first-class working atmosphere which is the very thing that helps to work fruitfully from the times when foundation stone was laid.</p>\r\n<p>The main motto of our company has always been our software products quality assurance. And it will remain unchanged. The standards of quality affect not only our professional services but also all other areas of our personnel daily life.</p>\r\n<p>For the first and the most it is the mutual and respectful communication and open amicable relations; interaction with customers based on trust and mutual respect, partnership and interest in the results of collaboration; ever-going investigation and deployment of innovative technologies, solutions and approaches for technical processes optimization; constant investments into growth of our staff''s professional level; effective and timely communication processes in the company on all levels - from regular workers to top-managers; drive for constant dynamic growth and self-perfection.</p>\r\n<p>Figure \"seven\" contains a magical power so we are sure that this year will be a real breakthrough for our company in the high-tech software solutions markets. We are active, young, world-class talented and positive about future.</p>\";}'),
  (594,191,111,'June 21, 2007'),
  (595,191,110,'Qulix Systems Has Celebrated its 7th Birthday'),
  (596,192,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:456:\"<p>Qulix Systems will be taking part in RUSSOFT Forum 2007, scheduled for June 20 - 22, 2007, Saint - Petersburg (Russia). Top-management of Qulix Systems has been always interested in obtaining and sharing outsourced software development expertise and such forums were always a valuable means for that. RUSSOFT Forum 2007 will provide IT executives with unique and valuable content to help them realize business value in their outsourcing engagements.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:2575:\"<h1>Qulix Systems Participates in RUSSOFT 2007</h1>\r\n<p>Qulix Systems will be taking part in RUSSOFT Forum 2007, scheduled for June 20 - 22, 2007, Saint - Petersburg (Russia). Top-management of Qulix Systems has been always interested in obtaining and sharing outsourced software development expertise and such forums were always a valuable means for that. RUSSOFT Forum 2007 will provide IT executives with unique and valuable content to help them realize business value in their outsourcing engagements.</p>\r\n<p>The global IT outsourcing industry is growing at an ever increasing pace, and with the growth comes change. The leading global vendors and the traditional outsourcing destinations are hard pressed to keep up with the new demands of the end users. Companies are driven to diversify their sourcing portfolios to spread risks and to look beyond Bangalore for specific value offerings that their businesses need to stay competitive and to succeed.</p>\r\n<p>The main purpose of the RUSSOFT Forum 2007 is to provide buyers of technology services from around the world with a better understanding of their sourcing options and to ensure higher return on their outsourcing investment through fostering lasting high value partnerships with leading service providers from Russia and Eastern Europe. It also serves as a platform to help Russian software service providers and ISVs showcase their services, products and solutions to the audience of analysts, potential clients and investors.</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"The event will offer presentations from prominent industry analysts and thought leaders, breakout sessions, and real-world case studies. Such forums are the source of acquisition and implementation of reliable alternative ways for providing quality and profitable results for our own outsourcing projects. Such events have been a real help during the last 7 years on the way to success of Qulix Systems\"</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Alexander Arabey, Director of Business Development</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"Eastern Europe has emerged as a strong outsourcing software development alternative to India for high value and complex software work. Qulix Systems is an international company with offices in UK and Russia though based in Belarus so b2b and particularly b2c cooperation is particularly close us. We have been successfully operating for years and know pitfalls to be aware of. But meeting partners and clients on such forums is not only a working necessity but a pleasure\"</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Alexey Makarov, CEO(Qulix Systems)</p>\";}'),
  (597,192,111,'June 15, 2007'),
  (598,192,110,'Qulix Systems Participates in RUSSOFT 2007'),
  (599,193,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:145:\"<p>Institute of Information Systems at the University of Hamburg and Qulix Systems company announce successful start of mutual collaboration.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:8132:\"<h1>Practical Insights into Global Outsourcing</h1>\r\n<p>Institute of Information Systems at the University of Hamburg and Qulix Systems company announce successful start of mutual collaboration.</p>\r\n<p>In period between 23rd April and 30th April there has been arranged a course of lectures and a seminar related to such topics as:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Global IT outsourcing from practical point of view;</li>\r\n<li>Country selection, Vendor selection;</li>\r\n<li>Interorganizational trust in global outsourcing relations;</li>\r\n<li>Quality Assurance in IT within outsourcing relations;</li>\r\n<li>Change Management in IT within outsourcing relations;</li>\r\n<li>Effects of cultural diversity in global IT relations.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The main idea of that course was to provide a combination of theoretical information about software development processes and global outsourcing trends, as well as to give certain practical insights onto these topics to selected students and the public of university. Within the course the goal was to demonstrate real-life process documents and tools. Both parties agree that such approach allows students and interested researchers to access unique knowledge about the best practices in global outsourcing which are implemented in reality and working, review successful and unsuccessful approaches to communication processes establishment and further aspects of the topic. The best results can be achieved when there is a reasonable combination of theory and practice as they are possible by the cooperation between the University and Qulix Systems.</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"By the cooperation with Qulix Systems we gain interesting insights into global outsourcing practice. The cooperation helps us to investigate new aspects of the topic and consider them as a useful part of our research agenda. Discussing the results of our research in the area of IT near- and offshore with experienced practitioners is of utmost importance.\"</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Prof. Dr. Stefan Voss, Chair and Director of the Institute of Information Systems (University of Hamburg)</p>\r\n<blockquote>or our students the lectures by Qulix Systems offer an insight view of practices of global IT outsourcing, a field of growing importance for the German IT sector. With a growing lack of IT experts in Germany, it is likely that a major share of our graduates will have to deal with global outsourcing activities in their professional career. So we understand the cooperation with Qulix Systems as a great chance to motivate and encourage our students to give attention to this important topic. The practical real-life experience Mr. Arabey shared with our students during the course of lectures in Hamburg is an important and motivating extension to our efforts on education our students in this sphere.\"</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Ronald Krick, Research &amp; Teaching Assistant (University of Hamburg)</p>\r\n<blockquote>\"The Seminar with Qulix Systems was characterised by a close linkage between theory and practice, which one did not expect in advance. The different stages of the software development process, which have play an important role in international outsourcing, were introduced as well as possible complications that can occur with the management of outsourcing activities. A positive surprise was the open discussion of typical problems within precontract negotiations with potentials outsourcers. As a possible solution Qulix introduced a clear strategy targeting on establishing trust and a long term relationship with their clients. Also the challenges a service provider is facing operation his international business from a transitional economy were touched. The experience within the sphere of outsourcing Qulix shared with us, which are affirmed by a survey undertaken by the Institute of Information Systems, as well as the up-to-date relevance of the topic open new paths and perspectives to us students.\"</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Andreas Rudi, student of economics</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>\"Our company has already been for 7 years in the area of outsourcing and software development and frankly speaking we have been involved in significant number of projects, which were driven not really efficiently from client''s side. So finally we decided to share some best and worst practices we have elaborated from our experience of participation in various outsourcing engagements. Of course we usually work very closely with our clients trying to establish the most appropriate processes in communication, requirements management and change management, acceptance procedures and so on. Nevertheless we think that the culture of business relations in outsourcing sphere is quite specific and it would be good to have certain knowledge before going into some collaboration and thus learning practical aspects in due course. We consider our current experience with University of Hamburg to be quite positive. Young people are potential future managers and some of them could be involved into outsourcing operations. The information we provided to them will definitely be useful and hopefully will contribute to the general success of their companies. But the success here is mutual, so Qulix will also benefit from efficient communication processes with its German customers in long term.</p>\r\n<p>For the moment, we are just starting our operations in Germany and probably will establish our office here somewhere in mid of 2008. Germany is developing very quickly and IT market is not an exception. Outsourcing of software development, quality assurance or some other operations is not widely spread yet, however we estimate its extreme growth in the coming years. We are very satisfied with this collaboration with University of Hamburg and probably we will jointly extend it in the nearest future. There are a number of projects we are considering now which include integration of scientific power of University and technical expertise of Qulix, and probably will be oriented initially on procurement, logistics, shipping and trading domains.\"</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p class=\"TextAlignRight\">Alexander Arabey,VP Business Development (Qulix Systems)</p>\r\n<h2>About University of Hamburg and the Institute of Information Systems</h2>\r\n<p>The Institute of Information Systems at the University of Hamburg headed by Prof. Dr. Voss is focused on the linkage of the three spheres research, teaching and practice. The key research areas automated negotiations in multi-agent based systems, Business Intelligence and Data Mining, E-Learning, modern optimization methods for decision support, Outsourcing, Supply Chain Management as well as Machine Translation and E-Governance are directly integrated into teaching and third-party funded practical projects. For improvement of teaching methods the Institute has participated in some university-spanning projects which have lead to implementation of modern teaching methods like Blended Learning. To offer students linkage to practice within their studies the institute maintains close relations to different enterprises. These relations allow the students to write practical oriented diploma theses and to participate in practical research projects.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.uni-hamburg.de/IWI\" target=\"_blank\">www.uni-hamburg.de/IWI</a></p>\r\n<p>With approximately 39,900 students, the University of Hamburg ranges fifth in size among the institutions of higher education in the Federal Republic of Germany. Corresponding to Hamburg''s view of itself as the \"gateway to the world\" the University with its diversity and traditions of subjects and educational offerings sees itself as the \"gateway to the world of knowledge\". It has 858 professors engaged in teaching and research, as well as an additional fulltime academic staff numbering 2,783. There are also 6,474 technical and administrative employees. About 1,000 part-time academic instructors teach at the University, and an equal number of additional academic and other employees are engaged in individual research projects financed by parties outside the University.</p>\";}'),
  (600,193,111,'May 10, 2007'),
  (601,193,110,'Practical Insights into Global Outsourcing'),
  (602,194,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:405:\"<p>The doors of Qulix Systems were opened all day long which gave the opportunity for 170 people to visit a company. Among the guests were students of Belarussian State University, Belarussian State University of Informatics and Radioelectronics, Belarussian National Technical University and other universities of Minsk starting from freshmen to seniors, professional developers &amp; QA specialists.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:3195:\"<h1>On the 25th of April an Open House Day Was Held at Qulix Systems</h1>\r\n<p>The doors of Qulix Systems were opened all day long which gave the opportunity for 170 people to visit a company. Among the guests were students of Belarussian State University, Belarussian State University of Informatics and Radioelectronics, Belarussian National Technical University and other universities of Minsk starting from freshmen to seniors, professional developers &amp; QA specialists.</p>\r\n<p>Open House Day has started with a press-conference where representatives of \"Computer News\", \"Facts &amp; Arguments in Belarus\", \"The Belarusians &amp; Market\", \"The Belarusian Time\" and internet-portals such as Kosht.com and Techlabs.by took part in the activity. Speakers at the meeting were CEO of Qulix Systems Alexey Makarov, Chief Operation Officer Valery Tikhonovich, and CEO of scientific-technical association \"Infopark\" Vladimir Basko.</p>\r\n<p>After the press-conference was conducted the first of three planned presentations was shown where Valery Tikhonovich has provided major information about general activities and goals of the company and answered the questions of guests.</p>\r\n<p>The doors of Qulix Systems were opened all day long which gave the opportunity for 170 people to visit the company. Among the guests were students of Belarussian State University, Belarussian State University of Informatics and Radioelectronics, Belarussian National Technical University and other universities of Minsk starting from freshmen to seniors, professional developers &amp; QA specialists.</p>\r\n<p>Every guest had an opportunity to take part in a guided tour over Qulix Systems office, receive answers to their questions from qualified consultants and had a conversation with CEO Alexey Makarov.</p>\r\n<p>The participants of meeting were very active and Chief of PR Department Valery Tikhonovich had a hard time answering the questions and providing the information about Qulix Systems. The students'' main question was about the possibility to combine study and work at session periods, about the opportunity of having practice &amp; trainings at the company, placement of graduates to Qulix Systems and requirements for applicants in software development and QA specialists.</p>\r\n<p>As for the professionals in software development, they have demonstrated high interest in technologies, current projects &amp; clients, near-term goals and perspectives of growth of Qulix Systems. Questions about requirements to project managers and experienced developers, career growth and freelance collaboration were also raised.</p>\r\n<p>The results are on hand. Right during presentations and guided tours the guests have expressed a wish to become a member of Qulix Systems'' team which gave an output of 50 filled in questionnaires and resumes mailed to us next day.</p>\r\n<p>It is worth saying that during the period of preparation for Open House Day the management of the company wasn''t expecting such an excitement and flurry among experienced software developers and qualified IT specialists .Today we can freely state that this event was useful both for our guests and clients and us, Qulix Systems team.</p>\";}'),
  (603,194,111,'May 02, 2007'),
  (604,194,110,'On the 25th of April an Open House Day Was Held at Qulix Systems'),
  (605,195,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"text\";s:255:\"<p>Qulix Systems invites you to meet us during the CeBIT fair which takes place in Hannover on 15-21 March. We exhibit directly in Outsourcing Area at boutique B22-10 and will be happy to discuss possible business relations and opportunities with you.</p>\";}'),
  (606,195,111,'March 12, 2007'),
  (607,195,110,'Meet Us on CeBIT 2007 in Hannover at Booth B22-10 in Outsourcing Pavilion'),
  (608,196,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"text\";s:448:\"<p>Qulix Systems announces unique opportunity for IT professionals and for people interested in IT sphere. We are opening our office for visits for the whole working day. Our top management will describe what is Qulix, what are our advantages, what we try to achieve, how a modern IT company should work and many other things. Meetings will take place on 25th April at 10AM, 2PM and 6PM in our Minsk office at Melnikayte 4, 607. You''re welcome!</p>\";}'),
  (609,196,111,'February 27, 2007'),
  (610,196,110,'Qulix Systems Announces Open House Day'),
  (611,197,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"text\";s:634:\"<p>Qulix Systems announced today, October 4, 2006 that the company will be moving into the new office, neighboring with the current location. Evidently, the firm out-grew the space of the office in use due to the rapid expansion and considerate increase of the employee number which, in turn, created a demand for a more spacious place. New office will give the company greater flexibility and room for expansion as needed. The new premises are now being equipped to best fit the needs of the company&rsquo;s employees and should be ready in one month. This will allow the working team to move to the new location by mid-November.</p>\";}'),
  (612,197,111,'November 04, 2006'),
  (613,197,110,'Qulix Systems Will Be Moving into the New Office'),
  (614,198,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"text\";s:266:\"<p>Qulix Systems announced today that a new representative office of the company was opened in the United Kingdom in September. The new establishment will now be officially representing the interests of the parent company in the territory of the hosting country.</p>\";}'),
  (615,198,111,'October 06, 2006'),
  (616,198,110,'New Representative Office of the Company Was Opened in the United Kingdom'),
  (617,199,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"text\";s:713:\"<p>Qulix Systems will be taking part in the annual trade show for information and telecommunications technology &ndash; CeBIT&rsquo;07, scheduled next year for March 15-21, Hannover (Germany). The company will be focusing on several aspects covered within the framework of the event: Communications, Banking &amp; Finance, Digital Systems and, thus, has already started preparing the participant&rsquo;s stand. The main objective of such engagement &ndash; to meet in person our partners and associates, as well as to acquire new business contacts in the region. Our participation in CeBIT will be followed by a country tour due to a number of planned meetings with partners, unable to be present at the show.</p>\";}'),
  (618,199,111,'September 14, 2006'),
  (619,199,110,'CEBIT''2007'),
  (620,200,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"text\";s:461:\"<p>Qulix Systems is currently planning to participate in Interop Moscow 2006, one of major IT-events in the Eastern Europe, this year scheduled for June 21-23. Main interest areas of our company, covered at the meeting include Enterprise Resource Planning software, Data Storage and Management Systems, Mobile/Wireless development, Information Security. We expect to be able to meet major IT and business technology buyers within the framework of the event.</p>\";}'),
  (621,200,111,'June 17, 2006'),
  (622,200,110,'Our Team Will Attend Interop Moscow 2006'),
  (623,201,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"text\";s:561:\"<p>As in the previous years, Qulix Systems participated in the annual Russian Outsourcing &amp; Software Summit 2006 (ROSS 2006). This year the event was held at the beginning of June in Moscow, Russia. Our team took part in various panels and speakers&rsquo; conferences, available to the attendees, as well as established valuable contacts with potential partners within B2B meetings. At the moment information acquired at the Summit is being processed, negotiations are held involving major software companies of both North American and European regions.</p>\";}'),
  (624,201,111,'June 14, 2006'),
  (625,201,110,'Qulix Systems Participates in ROSS 2006'),
  (626,202,112,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:0:\"\";s:4:\"text\";s:310:\"<p>Several days ago our company have started a new promising cooperation with a large Scandinavian company. The first project which is agreed for joint execution is the development of GPS based navigation system for mobile devices. It is expected to continue and extend this fruitful cooperation in future.</p>\";}'),
  (627,202,111,'February 02, 2005'),
  (628,202,110,'Qulix Systems Extends its Position on the Market of Software Development for Mobile Devices'),
  (629,203,114,'~ 400 hours'),
  (630,203,113,'Unified Document Management System'),
  (631,203,115,'2 specialists'),
  (632,203,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:255:\"<p>The test project featured a workflow management application for a government agency. The web application is based on EMC Documentum and includes three main modules: app server (Apache Tomcat, Linux), content server (AIX), and database server (AIX).</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1517:\"<h1>Unified Document Management System</h1>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>The test project featured a workflow management application for a government agency. The web application is based on EMC Documentum and includes three main modules: app server (Apache Tomcat, Linux), content server (AIX), and database server (AIX).</p>\r\n<p>The project aimed to track performance index upon new versions release, analyse and eliminate bottlenecks, estimate the load limit value in specific operating conditions.</p>\r\n<p>The established process enabled timely response to changes in application performance, meaning that inadequate functionality never reached the End Customer. The data obtained in the course of testing helped promptly identify the causes of performance decline, and consequently reduce the costs of their elimination. Besides response time check, the tests checked OS performance for each server (via built-in SAR utility).</p>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Performance testing: HP LoadRunner, SAR;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest;</li>\r\n<li>Reporting: MS Word, MS Excel.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Load model, load test strategy;</li>\r\n<li>Load test scripts and test case suites;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Test manager, 1 specialist in load testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 400 hours</p>\";}'),
  (633,204,114,'~ 13,000 hours (3years)'),
  (634,204,113,'Enterprise Billing System for Mobile Network Operator'),
  (635,204,115,'4 specialists'),
  (636,204,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:103:\"<p>The scope of project work included testing of a billing system that belong to a mobile operator.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1314:\"<h1>Enterprise Billing System for Mobile Network Operator</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web, enterprise billing system.</p>\r\n<h2>System Description</h2>\r\n<p>The project passed through the following stages:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Replacement of the current billing system;</li>\r\n<li>Development and customization of new service plans.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Key System Features:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Call control and online billing for pre-paid services;</li>\r\n<li>Network performance and user actions statistics collection, post-paid services tariffication;</li>\r\n<li>Network services configuration;</li>\r\n<li>Customer billing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration);</li>\r\n<li>Load testing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Load testing: HP LoadRunner;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: BugZilla.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Load model;</li>\r\n<li>Load test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Scripts;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>1 project manager, 2-3 functional software testing engineers, 1 specialist in functional and load automated testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 13,000 hours (3years).</p>\";}'),
  (637,205,114,'~ 10 000 hours'),
  (638,205,113,'EMC Documentum-Based Enterprise Workflow System'),
  (639,205,115,'5 specialists'),
  (640,205,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:140:\"<p>The goal of the project was to create an integrated comprehensive planning and control workflow system for a Russian energy provider.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1575:\"<h1>EMC Documentum-Based Enterprise Workflow System</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web, ECM (Enterprise Content Management).</p>\r\n<h2>System Description</h2>\r\n<p>The goal of the project was to create an integrated comprehensive planning and control workflow system for a Russian energy provider.</p>\r\n<p>Main features of the system include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Automation of document order execution control;</li>\r\n<li>Automation of standard document management processes;</li>\r\n<li>Creation of a unified and secure document repository.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration, usability, security);</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional testing;</li>\r\n<li>Non-functional testing (load, performance, volume, stress, reliability).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional testing: HP WinRunner;</li>\r\n<li>Load testing: HP LoadRunner;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Test plan, strategy;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional testing framework;</li>\r\n<li>Load model;</li>\r\n<li>Load test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Functional and load test scripts;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>1 project manager, 1-2 functional software testing engineers, 1-2 specialists in functional and load automated testing, flexible asset management.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 10 000 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (641,206,114,'~ 42,000 hours (~4 years)'),
  (642,206,113,'Unified Document Management System'),
  (643,206,115,'9 specialists'),
  (644,206,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:184:\"<p>The Customer (a major government entity) faced the fact that their written in C and client-server-based document management system was out of date and required through revision.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:2506:\"<h1>Unified Document Management System</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web, ECM (Enterprise Content Management)</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>The Customer (a major government entity) faced the fact that their written in C and client-server-based document management system was out of date and required through revision. Moreover, department modules were not mutually integrated which led to serious delays in document flow inside the organization.</p>\r\n<p>The Client&rsquo;s system needed drastic revision including database redesign and data porting with department modules integratable into a unified system.</p>\r\n<p>System development and data migration services were provided by Qulix Systems, whereas Qulix QA conducted complete independent testing of the given system all through its development life cycle.</p>\r\n<p>The project was aimed to implement and test the following system modules:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Registration of primary and secondary documentation specific to each module (incoming and outgoing correspondence, proceedings reports, minutes, citizens&rsquo; letters, responses, assignments, etc.)</li>\r\n<li>Document order execution control;</li>\r\n<li>Automatic reporting, generation and print of document references;</li>\r\n<li>Data cleaning and search functions;</li>\r\n<li>Introduction of the organization-and-establishment company structure;</li>\r\n<li>Inter-department and inter-organisation document tracking;</li>\r\n<li>Choosing and saving system interface settings on a user machine.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Work Conducted</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Business analysis;</li>\r\n<li>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration, usability, security);</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional testing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Words;</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional testing: HP QTP;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest / Atlassian Jira.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional requirements specification;</li>\r\n<li>Design specification;</li>\r\n<li>Test plan, strategy;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional testing framework;</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional test scripts;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>1 project manager, 3 business analysts, 4 specialists in functional testing, 1 specialist in functional automated testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 42,000 hours (~4 years).</p>\";}'),
  (645,207,114,'~ 1 000 hours'),
  (646,207,113,'Alfresco Pilot. Contract Document Management System Prototype'),
  (647,207,115,'3 specialists'),
  (648,207,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:115:\"<p>The goal of the project was to create a contract document management system prototype based on Alfresco EMC.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1821:\"<h1>Alfresco Pilot. Contract Document Management System Prototype</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web, ECM (Enterprise Content Management).</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>The goal of the project was to create a contract document management system prototype based on Alfresco EMC.</p>\r\n<p>Main system features:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Registration of documents;</li>\r\n<li>Document lifecycle tracking;</li>\r\n<li>Set-up of routing slips for document circulation;</li>\r\n<li>Working with document templates;</li>\r\n<li>Electronic document management.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Qulix QA provided a business analyst and a specialist in functional testing.</p>\r\n<p>The business analyst&rsquo;s main tasks included:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Analysis and specification of requirements of the Russian investors;</li>\r\n<li>Design of a functional specification;</li>\r\n<li>Update of the specification to fit the requirement changes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The functional testing specialist saw to the development of test documentation, testing of new system features, and regression testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Work Conducted</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Business analysis;</li>\r\n<li>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Design of a functional specification: MS Word, MS Visio;</li>\r\n<li>Browsers: IE7, IE8, Opera 9.64, Opera 10.10, FF 3.0, FF 3.5, Google Chrome 2.0;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional requirements specification;</li>\r\n<li>Test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Test manager, 1 business analyst, 1 specialist in functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 1,000 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (649,208,114,'~ 2 000 hours'),
  (650,208,113,'ABS Mortgage Lending'),
  (651,208,115,'4 specialists'),
  (652,208,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:78:\"<p>The scope of project work included testing of the ABS Mortgage Lending.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1026:\"<h1>ABS Mortgage Lending</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web, ABS (Automated Banking System)</p>\r\n<h2>System Description</h2>\r\n<p>The scope of project work included testing of the ABS Mortgage Lending.</p>\r\n<p>The system has the following features:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Submission and review of electronic loan applications;</li>\r\n<li>Generation of bank documents for loan transaction;</li>\r\n<li>Reporting;</li>\r\n<li>Administration;</li>\r\n<li>Management and control;</li>\r\n<li>Monitoring.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<p>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration, usability, security).</p>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: Atlassian Jira.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>1 project manager, 1-3 specialists in functional testing (flexible asset management).</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 2000 hours</p>\";}'),
  (653,209,114,'~ 650 hours'),
  (654,209,113,'Customer Service Automation System for GBA Bank Outlets'),
  (655,209,115,'2 specialists'),
  (656,209,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:59:\"<p>Automated banking system is used for retail banking.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1105:\"<h1>Customer Service Automation System for GBA Bank Outlets</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web, Banking System.</p>\r\n<h2>System Description</h2>\r\n<p>Automated banking system is used for retail banking.</p>\r\n<p>The system has the following main features:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Customer database management;</li>\r\n<li>Online service &ndash; handling banking transactions on behalf of a customer;</li>\r\n<li>Administration;</li>\r\n<li>Management and control;</li>\r\n<li>Monitoring.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Accessory features:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Log view;</li>\r\n<li>View of card products and customer requests;</li>\r\n<li>View and print of processed banking transactions register;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<p>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration, usability, security).</p>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: Atlassian Jira.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>1 project manager, 1 specialist in functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 650 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (657,210,114,'~ 1 000 hours'),
  (658,210,113,'Workflow Automation for a Government Agency'),
  (659,210,115,'3 specialists'),
  (660,210,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:102:\"<p>The system automates such business processes as planning, audit, internal document circulation.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1411:\"<h1>Workflow Automation for a Government Agency</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web, ECM (Enterprise Content Management).</p>\r\n<h2>System Description</h2>\r\n<p>The system automates such business processes as planning, audit, internal document circulation, and tasking and incorporates the following features:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\"Planning and Follow-up\" for asset management and manpower planning;</li>\r\n<li>\"Information\" for collecting, storing and editing of glossaries, guidelines and reference manuals;</li>\r\n<li>\"Task Management\" &ndash; the module fulfils control functions;</li>\r\n<li>\"Office Suite\" for standard office tasks automation;</li>\r\n<li>\"Administration\" for user management, access rights distribution and system settings.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional testing (system, regression, integration, configuration, usability, security);</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional testing;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional testing: HP WinRunner;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Scripts;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Team leader, 1 specialist in functional testing, 1 test automation specialist.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 1,000 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (661,211,114,'~ 300 hours'),
  (662,211,113,'UNICEF HIV Database'),
  (663,211,115,'1 specialist'),
  (664,211,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:142:\"<p>HIV Database contains information on HIV-infected patients. The system serves to store and analyse data on the spread of HIV infection.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:999:\"<h1>UNICEF HIV Database</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web, information database</p>\r\n<h2>System Description</h2>\r\n<p>HIV Database contains information on HIV-infected patients. The system serves to store and analyse data on the spread of HIV infection and incorporates the following features:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Administration;</li>\r\n<li>Patient registration;</li>\r\n<li>Clinical study results storing;</li>\r\n<li>Advanced search;</li>\r\n<li>Data import/export;</li>\r\n<li>Report generation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<p>Functional testing (system, regression, integration, configuration, usability, security).</p>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>1 specialist in functional software testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 300 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (665,212,114,'~ 250 hours'),
  (666,212,113,'WCS – Wildlife Conservation Society'),
  (667,212,115,'1 specialist'),
  (668,212,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:66:\"<p>The project was aimed to expand the WCS information portal.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1204:\"<h1>WCS &ndash; Wildlife Conservation Society</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web, information system.</p>\r\n<h2>System Description</h2>\r\n<p>The project was aimed to expand the WCS information portal.</p>\r\n<p>System Features</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Virus database, description of specimens, diagnostic tests, and tools;</li>\r\n<li>Reference data on institutions engaged in virus research;</li>\r\n<li>Administration: access rights distribution and control;</li>\r\n<li>Advanced search;</li>\r\n<li>Export of data;</li>\r\n<li>Configuration, structuring and batching of data;</li>\r\n<li>Implementation of the architectural solution to run several application bodies from different databases using similar logic.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<p>Functional testing (system, regression, integration, configuration, usability, security).</p>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>1 specialist in functional software testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 250 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (669,213,114,'~ 600 hours'),
  (670,213,113,'HR Management Automation'),
  (671,213,115,'2 specialists'),
  (672,213,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:163:\"<p>The goal of the project was to update the Microsoft SharePoint Server-based corporate portal of a mobile network operator to provide flexible HR management.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:753:\"<h1>HR Management Automation</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web, HRM (Human Resources Management).</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>The goal of the project was to update the Microsoft SharePoint Server-based corporate portal of a mobile network operator to provide flexible HR management.</p>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<p>Functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>1 test manager, 1 specialist in functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 600 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (673,214,114,'~ 350 hours'),
  (674,214,113,'CRBT (Calling Ring Back Tone)'),
  (675,214,115,'3 specialists'),
  (676,214,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:229:\"<p>The project was aimed to test a CRBT (Calling Ring Back Tone) service provided by a mobile network operator. Service users can change a telephone line ring-back tone for set callers from standard signals to selected tunes.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1503:\"<h1>CRBT (calling ring back tone)</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web, VAS (Value-Added Service)</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>The project was aimed to test a CRBT (calling ring back tone) service provided by a mobile network operator. Service users can change a telephone line ring-back tone for set callers from standard signals to selected tunes.</p>\r\n<p>Key service setting system features:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>CRBT service activation/deactivation;</li>\r\n<li>User music track list management;</li>\r\n<li>User caller list management (playing a set tune for a set caller);</li>\r\n<li>Track list search;</li>\r\n<li>Adding tracks from the library and music charts to user track lists.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Business analysis;</li>\r\n<li>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration, integration, usability).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Design of a functional specification: MS Word, MS Visio;</li>\r\n<li>Browsers: IE7, IE8, Opera 9.64, FF 3.0, FF 3.5, Google Chrome 2.0</li>\r\n<li>Test schedule and methodology: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional requirements specification;</li>\r\n<li>Test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Test schedule and methodology;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Test manager, 1 business analyst, 1 specialist in functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 350 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (677,215,114,'~ 5,200 hours (6 months)'),
  (678,215,113,'Computer People, Office Angels'),
  (679,215,115,'6 specialists'),
  (680,215,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:106:\"<p>The goal of the project was to create a system for vacancy posting and job search in Great Britain.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1676:\"<h1>Computer People, Office Angels</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web, E-business.</p>\r\n<h2>System Description</h2>\r\n<p>The system was developed for a major British consulting agency.</p>\r\n<p>The goal of the project was to create a system for vacancy posting and job search in Great Britain.</p>\r\n<p>The system incorporates three basic subsystems:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Administration and content management;</li>\r\n<li>Recruiting system for IT personnel selection;</li>\r\n<li>Recruiting system for office personnel selection.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Each of the subsystems is individually branded and has its unique design.</p>\r\n<p>Key system features include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Applicants login;</li>\r\n<li>CV creation, posting and management;</li>\r\n<li>Employers login;</li>\r\n<li>Vacancies creation, posting and management;</li>\r\n<li>Personal area;</li>\r\n<li>Invitation to view vacancies/CVs;</li>\r\n<li>Reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration, usability, security);</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional testing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional testing: HP WinRunner;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: customer development.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Test plan, strategy;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Automated test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Framework;</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional test scripts;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>1 team leader, 2 specialists in functional testing, 3 specialists in automated testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 5,200 hours (6 months).</p>\";}'),
  (681,216,114,'~ 200 hours'),
  (682,216,113,'Career Person, Build Team'),
  (683,216,115,'4 specialists'),
  (684,216,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:99:\"<p>The goal of the project was to create a system for vacancy posting and job search in Russia.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:988:\"<h1>Career Person, Build Team</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web, E-business.</p>\r\n<h2>System Description</h2>\r\n<p>The goal of the project was to create a system for vacancy posting and job search in Russia.</p>\r\n<p>Key system features include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Applicants login;</li>\r\n<li>CV creation, posting and management;</li>\r\n<li>Employers login;</li>\r\n<li>Vacancies creation, posting and management;</li>\r\n<li>Personal area.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<p>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration, usability, security).</p>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Test cases: Mercury Quality Center (Test Director);</li>\r\n<li>Change management: Mercury Quality Center (Test Director).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software Quality Reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>1 project manager, 1-3 specialists in functional testing (flexible asset management).</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 200 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (685,217,114,'~ 1 100 hours'),
  (686,217,113,'Dot Mobile'),
  (687,217,115,'1 specialist'),
  (688,217,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:144:\"<p>The system is a technical layout of web pages with a varying number of units containing text, graphics, interactive and dynamic elements.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1097:\"<h1>Dot Mobile</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web.</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>The system is a technical layout of web pages with a varying number of units containing text, graphics, interactive and dynamic elements.</p>\r\n<p>The team was tasked with testing the web pages layout as to their correct display and behaviour during page cropping, browser zooming, etc.</p>\r\n<p>The project included testing of TV and NET types of page layout.</p>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<p>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration).</p>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>VMware for OS operation: Windows XP, Windows Vista, Mac OS, Linux</li>\r\n<li>Browsers: Firefox, IE6, IE7, Opera, Safari, Konqueror, Camino, Google Chrome</li>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: Unfuddle.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>1 specialist in functional software testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 1,100 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (689,218,114,'~ 350 hours'),
  (690,218,113,'IGRING Game Portal'),
  (691,218,115,'4 specialists'),
  (692,218,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:70:\"<p>The project was aimed to test a web portal dedicated to gaming.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:994:\"<h1>IGRING Game Portal</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web, Entertainment.</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>The project was aimed to test a web portal dedicated to gaming.</p>\r\n<p>Key portal features include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reporting game industry news;</li>\r\n<li>New games announcements and description;</li>\r\n<li>Interactive games;</li>\r\n<li>Game-addicts chat;</li>\r\n<li>Login and personal area for regular members;</li>\r\n<li>Polls, voting, comments.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<p>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration, usability).</p>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Test manager, 1-3 specialists in functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 350 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (693,219,114,'~ 420 hours'),
  (694,219,113,'Stored Procedures Testing System'),
  (695,219,115,'3 specialists'),
  (696,219,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:86:\"<p>The project was aimed to test the system used for testing of stored procedures.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1433:\"<h1>Stored Procedures Testing System</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web.</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>The project was aimed to test the system used for testing of stored procedures.</p>\r\n<p>Key system features include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Loading stored procedures into the system for tests;</li>\r\n<li>Implementing stored procedures with varying input parameters;</li>\r\n<li>Analysing input parameters, comparing them with the standards;</li>\r\n<li>Creating sets of stored procedures for testing;</li>\r\n<li>Generating test reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Work Conducted</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Business analysis (development of a functional specification and system graphic interface design);</li>\r\n<li>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration, usability, security);</li>\r\n<li>Elaboration of a user manual.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Functional requirements specification: MS Visio, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest;</li>\r\n<li>User manual: MS Word.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional requirements specification;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports;</li>\r\n<li>User manual.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Test manager, 1 business analyst, 1 specialist in functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 420 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (697,220,114,'~ 250 hours'),
  (698,220,113,'File Transfer System (File Sharing Server)'),
  (699,220,115,'2 specialists'),
  (700,220,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:94:\"<p>A platform for allocating, sharing, uploading and sending large files via the Internet.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:809:\"<h1>File Transfer System (File Sharing Server)</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web.</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>A platform for allocating, sharing, uploading and sending large files via the Internet.</p>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration);</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional testing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional testing: WatiN;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: Gemini.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Test manager, 1 specialist in functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 250 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (701,221,114,'~ 1200 hours'),
  (702,221,113,'MobiFly Auto'),
  (703,221,115,'3 specialists'),
  (704,221,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:262:\"<p>The goal of the project was to create a competitive automated mobile content delivery and management system for major auto dealing businesses over the company&rsquo;s own product &ndash; a universal service platform MCDN (Mobile Content Delivery Network).</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:2064:\"<h1>MobiFly Auto</h1>\r\n<div class=\"LeftImg\"><img width=\"533px\" height=\"174px\" src=\"/uploaded/image/screens/MobiflyAuto.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web / Mobile.</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>The goal of the project was to create a competitive automated mobile content delivery and management system for major auto dealing businesses over the company&rsquo;s own product &ndash; a universal service platform MCDN (Mobile Content Delivery Network).</p>\r\n<p>Main Features of MobiFly Auto:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>System access management at the actual business structure roles level;</li>\r\n<li>Secure SSL connection for safe confidential data transmission for both web and mobile communication sessions;</li>\r\n<li>Target group management so as to find potential clients for further sales promotion;</li>\r\n<li>Categorized catalogue of goods and services set up with respect to the target audience offering a flexible keyword search option;</li>\r\n<li>A fully adjustable polling/voting subsystem which allows users to obtain poll/vote results once the action is over;</li>\r\n<li>A subsystem for creating, distributing and tracing the use of discount cards for certain goods and services inside the system;</li>\r\n<li>A financial module for handy intersystem money transactions record.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Work Conducted</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Business analysis (development of a functional specification and system graphic interface design);</li>\r\n<li>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration, usability).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Functional requirements specification: MS Visio, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional requirements specification;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Test manager, 2 specialists in functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 1200 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (705,222,114,'~ 1320 hours'),
  (706,222,113,'Continium Automated Energy Monitoring and Accounting System'),
  (707,222,115,'4 specialists'),
  (708,222,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:160:\"<p>The system serves for automated recording, accumulation, and processing of energy meters readings within communal services and manufacturing enterprises.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1528:\"<h1>Continium Automated Energy Monitoring and Accounting System</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web.</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>The system serves for automated recording, accumulation, and processing of energy meters readings within communal services and manufacturing enterprises.</p>\r\n<p>The automated energy monitoring and accounting system offers the possibility to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To take gas, electricity, cold and hot water meter readings;</li>\r\n<li>To collect information on consumption of resources within the system;</li>\r\n<li>To manage the structure of record objects and data acquisition units;</li>\r\n<li>To analyse resource consumption through reports, tables and graphics.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Work Conducted</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration, usability);</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional testing;</li>\r\n<li>Elaboration of a user manual.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional testing: Segue SilkTest;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest</li>\r\n<li>User manual: MS Word.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional test scripts;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports;</li>\r\n<li>User manual.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Test manager, 2 specialists in functional testing, 1 specialist in automated functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 1320 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (709,223,114,'~ 520 hours'),
  (710,223,113,'Reference Data System for Branch Business Units'),
  (711,223,115,'3 specialists'),
  (712,223,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:116:\"<p>Reference data system for branch business units serves for automation of enterprise data resource management.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1064:\"<h1>Reference Data System for Branch Business Units</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web, ECM (Enterprise Content Management).</p>\r\n<h2>System Description</h2>\r\n<p>Reference data system for branch business units serves for automation of enterprise data resource management:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Keeping records for business property objects;</li>\r\n<li>Registration of investment contracts;</li>\r\n<li>Count of members of the board of directors;</li>\r\n<li>Measurement of company financial standing indices;</li>\r\n<li>Using reference books;</li>\r\n<li>Reports generation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<p>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration, usability).</p>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: FogBugz.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional test plans;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Test manager, 2 specialists in functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 520 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (713,224,114,'~ 340 hours'),
  (714,224,113,'Testing of a Billing Module for a Payment System'),
  (715,224,115,'2 specialists'),
  (716,224,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:100:\"<p>The project was aimed to test a billing component of the Internet credit card payment system.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:962:\"<h1>Testing of a Billing Module for a Payment System</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web, billing system.</p>\r\n<h2>System Description</h2>\r\n<p>The project was aimed to test a billing component of the Internet credit card payment system.</p>\r\n<p>Key features of the module include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Processing of incoming transactions;</li>\r\n<li>Management of tariffs and currency exchange rates (creation, modification and deletion of respective objects).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<p>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration, usability).</p>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: Atlassian Jira.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Test manager, 1 specialist in functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 340 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (717,225,114,'~ 1000 hours'),
  (718,225,113,'Workflow Automation for a Government Agency (Information Analysis System KRD)'),
  (719,225,115,'3 specialists'),
  (720,225,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:200:\"<p>The system serves for automation of activities of the control and audit office, and specifically planning and implementation of inspection and review measures and internal document circulation.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:2082:\"<h1>Workflow Automation for a Government Agency (Information Analysis System KRD)</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web, ECM (Enterprise Content Management).</p>\r\n<h2>System Description</h2>\r\n<p>The Customer is a federal state unitary enterprise.</p>\r\n<p>The system serves for automation of activities of the control and audit office, and specifically planning and implementation of inspection and review measures and internal document circulation.</p>\r\n<p>The purpose of the system is to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Standardise and  automate the existing records management process;</li>\r\n<li>Enhance efficiency and appropriateness of budget expenditures;</li>\r\n<li>Provide information and analytical support of primary activities of the control and audit office;</li>\r\n<li>Speed up reconciliation and operation processes;</li>\r\n<li>Boost efficiency of document management;</li>\r\n<li>Facilitate processes of rational management decision making.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The system incorporates the following features:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\"Planning and Follow-up\" for asset management and manpower planning;</li>\r\n<li>\"Information\" for collecting, storing and editing of glossaries, guidelines and reference manuals;</li>\r\n<li>\"Task Management\" to fulfil control functions;</li>\r\n<li>\"Office Suite\" for standard office tasks automation;</li>\r\n<li>\"Administration\" for user management, access rights distribution and system settings.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional testing (system, regression, integration, configuration, usability, security);</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional testing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional testing: HP WinRunner;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Scripts;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Team leader, 1 specialist in functional testing, 1 test automation specialist.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 1,000 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (721,226,114,'~ 840 hours'),
  (722,226,113,'Payment System'),
  (723,226,115,'2 specialists'),
  (724,226,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:124:\"<p>The project involved development of a payment processing system for making payments via the Internet or mobile phone.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1381:\"<h1>Payment System</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Web, Mobile, Payment System</p>\r\n<h2>System Description</h2>\r\n<p>The project involved development of a payment processing system for making payments via the Internet or mobile phone.</p>\r\n<p>Main system features include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Using mobile account funds (web, midlet);</li>\r\n<li>Using funds from bank card accounts (web, midlet);</li>\r\n<li>Billing and payment options from service providers;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<p>1. Automated functional testing using Java (jdk 1.6) + Selenium and Selenium IDE.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Design of automated functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Framework design;</li>\r\n<li>Development of test automation scripts;</li>\r\n<li>Delivery and analysis of test results as outlined in project plan.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>2. Functional Testing.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Design of test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Comprehensive functional testing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Test automation: Selenium IDE.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Automated test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Automated test scripts;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>2 leading specialists in functional testing and test automation.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 840 hours</p>\";}'),
  (725,227,114,'~ 10,000 hours (~4 years)'),
  (726,227,113,'Hedge Funds Management System'),
  (727,227,115,'5 specialists'),
  (728,227,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:106:\"<p>The Customer is a Swiss company seeking to maintain its dominant position on the hedge fund market.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1307:\"<h1>Hedge Funds Management System</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Desktop, Financial.</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>The Customer is a Swiss company seeking to maintain its dominant position on the hedge fund market. The goal of the project was to create a system for investment management, risk analysis, strategic planning and statistical analysis.</p>\r\n<p>The HF Optimizer platform incorporates three modules:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Investment portfolio construction;</li>\r\n<li>Hedge fund selection;</li>\r\n<li>ROI forecast.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Work Conducted</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Business analysis;</li>\r\n<li>Functional testing (system, regression, integration, configuration, usability, installation).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Design of a functional specification: MS Word, MS Visio;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel + HP Quality Center (Test Director);</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional requirements specification;</li>\r\n<li>Test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Test manager, 1-3 specialists in functional testing, 1 business analyst.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 10,000 hours (~4 years).</p>\";}'),
  (729,228,114,'~ 5,000 hours (12 months)'),
  (730,228,113,'BioNuclear Process Analysis System'),
  (731,228,115,'4 specialists'),
  (732,228,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:167:\"<p>The system was designed for the consortium of the BioPat project with the purpose of creating a unified database named Collaborative Knowledge Repository (CKR).</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1439:\"<h1>BioNuclear Process Analysis System</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Desktop, scientific analysis application</p>\r\n<h2>System Description</h2>\r\n<p>The system was designed for the consortium of the BioPat project with the purpose of creating a unified database named Collaborative Knowledge Repository (CKR). The system is based on the use of the Process Analysis Technology (PAT) developed in the framework of the Improvement of the Bioanalysis Tools programme.</p>\r\n<p>The application incorporates three modules:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>CKR database;</li>\r\n<li>Visualisation and CKR data management subsystem;</li>\r\n<li>CKR analysis subsystem.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional testing (system, regression, installation, configuration, localization);</li>\r\n<li>Non-functional testing (performance, volume, stress, reliability).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Load testing: HP LoadRunner;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Test plan, strategy;</li>\r\n<li>Load test model, strategy and plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional and load test scripts;</li>\r\n<li>Load test scripts;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>1 team leader, 2 specialists in functional testing, 1 specialist in automated testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 5,000 hours (12 months).</p>\";}'),
  (733,229,114,'~4 000 hours'),
  (734,229,113,'Automated Banking Systems Integration'),
  (735,229,115,'4 specialists'),
  (736,229,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:157:\"<p>The system is used for bank customer database management. It registers and stores individual customer profiles, miscellaneous accounts and bank cards.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1379:\"<h1>Automated Banking Systems Integration</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Desktop, Banking System.</p>\r\n<h2>System Description</h2>\r\n<p>The system is used for bank customer database management. It registers and stores individual customer profiles, miscellaneous accounts and bank cards. The system was integrated with other automated banking systems (mutual funds, non-state pension funds, etc.).</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>The system practically lacked documentation, which hampered its maintenance and further development. The project was mainly aimed at reverse engineering of the system. which ran parallel to system development activities.</p>\r\n<h2>Work Conducted</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Business analysis;</li>\r\n<li>Functional testing (system, regression, integration, configuration, usability, security).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Requirements management, test cases and test suites design, test management, change management: HP Quality Centre (Test Director).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional requirements specification;</li>\r\n<li>Scope stetement;</li>\r\n<li>Test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Test manager, 1 business analyst, 2 specialists in functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 4,000 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (737,230,114,'~ 80 hours'),
  (738,230,113,'Automated Functional Testing of Bank Transfer Transactions'),
  (739,230,115,'1 specialist'),
  (740,230,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:93:\"<p>A VB client-server application that uses an Oracle database was subject to automation.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1340:\"<h1>Automated Functional Testing of Bank Transfer Transactions</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Desktop, , Banking System.</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>A VB client-server application that uses an Oracle database was subject to automation. Automation was implemented on HP Quality Centre (Test Director) and HP QuickTest Professional 10 basis. The automation system represented the implementation of a keyword driven framework. Descriptive programming was employed for application object identification.</p>\r\n<p>Work Conducted</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Development of scripts;</li>\r\n<li>HP Quality Centre (Test Director) -assisted implementation of a distributed multiple-machine script start;</li>\r\n<li>Modification of logging processes (technical refinement, introduction of changes relative to the distributed start).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Design of test cases and test suites, implementation of automated script start HP Quality Centre (Test Director);</li>\r\n<li>Test Automation HP QuickTestProfessional 10.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Automated test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional testing framework;</li>\r\n<li>Automated functional test scripts;</li>\r\n<li>Logging mechanism.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>1 specialist in automated testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 80 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (741,231,114,'380 hours'),
  (742,231,113,'Master Trend SCADA'),
  (743,231,115,'3 specialists'),
  (744,231,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:125:\"<p>The subject of testing was a SCADA application for collection, analysis and reporting of data on equipment performance</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1977:\"<h1>Master Trend SCADA</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Desktop, SCADA.</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>The subject of testing was a SCADA application for collection, analysis and reporting of data on equipment performance . The project included testing of a module for drawing graphs handling both archived and real time data.</p>\r\n<p>The goal of the project was to conduct functional and load testing of the system before it was put into industrial operation.</p>\r\n<p>As part of non-functional testing activities the team was tasked with the assessment of application performance during graph drawing operations (zooming, scrolling, value range and time intervals changing, etc.) and impact of each single operation on different OSes (Windows XP and Windows Vista) on system performance. The task was implemented through Ranorex tool (for application work) and Windows Performance Counter (for monitoring).</p>\r\n<p>Reports commenting on overall system performance and each of the specified system operations were compiled upon project completion. Other reports included analytical reports for each OS and a cross report comparing the two operation systems. The project helped indicate the scope of memory leak problems.</p>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration);</li>\r\n<li>Performance testing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Performance testing Ranorex, Windows Performance Counter;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Load test model, strategy and plan;</li>\r\n<li>Load test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Scripts;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Test manager, 1 specialist in functional testing, 1 specialist in load testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 380 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (745,232,114,'~ 8,000 hours (3 years)'),
  (746,232,113,'Wayfinder GPS Navigator'),
  (747,232,115,'2 specialists'),
  (748,232,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:61:\"<p>Wayfinder GPS Navigator is a global navigation system.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1400:\"<h1>Wayfinder GPS Navigator</h1>\r\n<div class=\"LeftImg\"><img width=\"358px\" height=\"177px\" src=\"/uploaded/image/screens/wayfinder.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Mobile, GPS navigation.</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>Wayfinder GPS Navigator is a global navigation system.</p>\r\n<p>Key System Features:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Map assisted current position tracking;</li>\r\n<li>Automatic routing;</li>\r\n<li>Route tracing;</li>\r\n<li>Access to travel information;</li>\r\n<li>En route voice commands;</li>\r\n<li>Multilingual interface and VoiceOver;</li>\r\n<li>Advanced search by address, object types (restaurant, museum, self-service terminal, stops, etc.).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The mobile app uses a remote server for map access, route generation, POI, etc.</p>\r\n<p>Support for Windows Mobile 2003, 5.0, 6.0 and 6.1 (Pocket PC and smartphones).</p>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<p>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration, installation, usability).</p>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest / Eventum;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Test manager, 1 specialist in functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 8,000 hours (3 years).</p>\";}'),
  (749,233,114,'~ 200 hours'),
  (750,233,113,'Thumbplayer'),
  (751,233,115,'1 specialist'),
  (752,233,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:143:\"<p>Thumbplayer is an application that allows users to search for music tracks, create playlists and lists of favourite artisits and albums.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1210:\"<h1>Thumbplayer</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Mobile, Media.</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>Thumbplayer is an application that allows users to search for music tracks, create playlists and lists of favourite artisits and albums.</p>\r\n<p>Main system features:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Track, artist, and album search;</li>\r\n<li>Playlist creation, editing, and deletion;</li>\r\n<li>Favourite artist and album list creation, editing, and deletion;</li>\r\n<li>Current session track list creation;</li>\r\n<li>Artist and album details display;</li>\r\n<li>Track hashing for flight mode playback.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The mobile app uses a remote server for getting and downloading tracks and getting track information.</p>\r\n<p>Supports iPhone and Android platforms.</p>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<p>Functional testing (regression, installation, usability).</p>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>1 specialist in functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 200 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (753,234,114,'~ 150 hours'),
  (754,234,113,'Lesmobilizers eBook'),
  (755,234,115,'1 specialist'),
  (756,234,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:76:\"<p>Lesmobilizers eBook is an application for reading the Le chemin book.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1116:\"<h1>Lesmobilizers eBook</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Mobile.</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>Lesmobilizers eBook is an application for reading the Le chemin book.</p>\r\n<p>Main System Features:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Chaptered book display with a page turning effect;</li>\r\n<li>Index of reading progress for each chapter;</li>\r\n<li>Default font size setting;</li>\r\n<li>Option for publishing book extracts to Twitter and Facebook;</li>\r\n<li>Option for sending a blurb;</li>\r\n<li>Option for buying new chapters;</li>\r\n<li>Flight mode support.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The mobile app uses a remote server for getting new chapters.</p>\r\n<p>Supported platform: iPhone.</p>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<p>Functional testing (regression, installation, usability).</p>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>1 specialist in functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 150 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (757,235,114,'670 hours'),
  (758,235,113,'Bluetooth Media Network'),
  (759,235,115,'2 specialists'),
  (760,235,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:156:\"<p>Bluetooth Media Network is a distributed multimedia network that delivers free multimedia content and commercial ads to mobile devices via Bluetooth.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1153:\"<h1>Bluetooth Media Network</h1>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Mobile.</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>Bluetooth Media Network is a distributed multimedia network that delivers free multimedia content and commercial ads to mobile devices via Bluetooth.</p>\r\n<p>Main system features include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sending multimedia content which does not require installation of additional software on user devices;</li>\r\n<li>Multi-user access and simultaneous operation for numerous Bluetooth adapters;</li>\r\n<li>Effective mobile device identification system;</li>\r\n<li>Synchronisation with distributed nodes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<p>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration, integration, usability).</p>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Test manager, 1 specialist in functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 670 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (761,236,114,'1200 hours'),
  (762,236,113,'TAPTX Mobile'),
  (763,236,115,'3 specialists'),
  (764,236,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:55:\"<p>TAPTX offers its users a range popular services.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1305:\"<h1>TAPTX Mobile</h1>\r\n<div class=\"LeftImg\"><img src=\"/uploaded/image/screens/taptx.jpg\" height=\"196px\" width=\"310px\" /></div>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Mobile.</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>TAPTX offers its users a range popular services:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>SMS exchange service Option to add Yahoo, Google Talk, MSN, AIM, ICQ user accounts;</li>\r\n<li>Access to numerous information resources (news, whether forecasts, travel info, currency exchange rates, etc.) from publicly-available information sources;</li>\r\n<li>Option to run advertising campaigns within the TAPTX community.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The system incorporates the following modules:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Application Server;</li>\r\n<li>DB Server;</li>\r\n<li>Content Server;</li>\r\n<li>Mobile Client.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<p>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration, integration, usability).</p>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Team leader, 2 specialists in functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 1200 hours.</p>\";}'),
  (765,237,114,'1 080 hours'),
  (766,237,113,'Mobile Services'),
  (767,237,115,'2 specialists'),
  (768,237,116,'a:2:{s:5:\"tizer\";s:278:\"<p>Mobile services is an entertainment resource offering a variety of services such as news reading, interactive viewing and loading of media content (pictures, audio, video), communication with other users via a built-in ICQ client, taking part in surveys, polls and tests.</p>\";s:4:\"text\";s:1353:\"<h1>Mobile services</h1>\r\n<div class=\"LeftImg\"><img width=\"232px\" height=\"176px\" src=\"/uploaded/image/screens/MobileServices.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<h2>Category</h2>\r\n<p>Mobile, VAS.</p>\r\n<h2>Distinctive Features of the Project</h2>\r\n<p>Mobile services is an entertainment resource offering a variety of services such as news reading, interactive viewing and loading of media content (pictures, audio, video), communication with other users via a built-in ICQ client, taking part in surveys, polls and tests.</p>\r\n<p>Each user has their personal area with an option to edit personal data and easily change their account settings for handy content management.</p>\r\n<p>System back-end contains functionality for system administration, user management, content delivery, statistical report generation, gathering and publishing of news.</p>\r\n<h2>Tests Conducted</h2>\r\n<p>Functional testing (system, regression, configuration, integration, usability).</p>\r\n<h2>Tools</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planning: MS Project, MS Word;</li>\r\n<li>Test cases: MS Excel;</li>\r\n<li>Change management: IBM Rational ClearQuest.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Artifacts</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Functional test plan;</li>\r\n<li>Functional test cases;</li>\r\n<li>Software quality reports.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Project Team</h2>\r\n<p>Test manager, 1 specialist in functional testing.</p>\r\n<h2>Effort</h2>\r\n<p>~ 1,080 hours.</p>\";}'),
